(269,'2FTISanDiego2016','**Getting to UCSD:**\r\n\r\nFrom south of the 52: Head north on the I5, take the Gilman exit and follow Gilman Drive all the way into the UCSD campus. Just after Russell Lane, you will see the Gilman parking structure on your left. Park here and walk north on Russell Lane, then left on Lyman. The Price Center will be on your right.\r\n\r\nFrom north of the 52: Head south on I5 and take the La Jolla Village Drive exit. Make a right at La Jolla Village Drive, and in 3/4 mile turn right onto Villa La Jolla Drive. Follow it into campus and it will lead you right to the Gilman parking structure. Park here, then walk north on Russell Lane, left on Lyman, and the Price Center will be on your right. Enter the building and take the stairs or the elevator to the 2nd floor and look for Ballroom AB (there will be signs set up for the competition).\r\n\r\n**Parking Information:**\r\nParking is free at UCSD on the weekends, but please park only in designated visitor parking areas, marked \"P\" on the campus map. Cars parked in spots marked \"24/7 Reserved\" may still be ticketed or towed.\r\n\r\n**Venue & Campus:**\r\nHere is a [campus map](http://maps.ucsd.edu/Acrobat/CampusMap.pdf). The Price Center is just southwest of University Center near the center of the campus map. Walking from Gilman parking, the stairs to Price Center Ballroom B will be west of the Triton fountain, but before you reach the bookstore. From the Price Center outside plaza, walk up the largest set of stairs. A map of Price Center can be found [here](http://universitycenters.ucsd.edu/images/main/maps/pclevel2.png). There will be restaurants open in the food court on the main floor. Please provide adult supervision for children under 12.',6,'Travel'),
(270,'2FTISanDiego2016','| Events | Format | Cutoff | Time Limit | R1 Person Limit | R2 Person Limit | Final Person Limit |\r\n| -------- | -------- | -------- | -------- | -------- | -------- | -------- | -------- |\r\n| **3x3**    | Avg of 5     | None     | 3:00 | 100 | 24 | 8 |\r\n| **3x3 One-handed**     | Avg of 5     | 0:45  | 3:00 | 100 | 24 | 8 |\r\n| **Megaminx**    | Avg of 5     | 2:00  | 5:00 | 100 | - | - |\r\n| **6x6 Speedsolve**    | Mean of 3     | 5:00     | 10:00 | 100 | - | - |\r\n| **7x7 Speedsolve**     | Mean of 3     | 7:00     | 10:00 | 100 | - | - |\r\n\r\n\\* **We will not be holding TeamBLD or Square-1.**\r\n\r\n*Cutoffs may change depending on competitor turnout.*\r\n\r\nYou must have a single solve under the listed cutoff time in the first two solves in order to complete the Average of 5. For 6x6 and 7x7, your first solve must be under the listed time in order to complete the Mean of 3.\r\n\r\nTime limits are hard cutoffs; solves will be stopped after the time limit is reached.',3,'Events'),
