(11558,'1stJorhatOpen2019','For those of you new to cubing, WELCOME!\r\n\r\nWe wanted to let you know this event is perfectly fine for cubers of ANY age and experience. We just ask you know a couple things before coming to compete...\r\n\r\nFirst, please be familiar with the WCA Regulations, found here:\r\nhttps://www.worldcubeassociation.org/regulations/\r\n\r\nThis video will explain most of what any cuber competing for the first time will need to know.\r\n\r\nyoutube(https://www.youtube.com/embed/dPL3eV-A0ww)\r\n\r\nIf you are stoked to compete and ready to sign up, head over to the \'Registration & Payment\' tab and it will guide you to the registration.\r\n\r\n**FAQs**\r\n\r\nQ: Do I use my own cube to compete?\r\nA: YES! You are responsible for your own hardware in order to compete. This means you should bring your own cube.\r\n\r\nQ: What is the normal age of competitors at these events?\r\nA: All ages are welcome, but in general competitors are between 10 and 20 years old. Don\'t let this stop you though, everyone can and should cube!\r\n\r\nQ: How do I find results?\r\nA: All results are posted on the WCA page within a week after the competition finishes. However, for the day of competing, go to Cubecomps.com to find information about current events. This is also where you will find information about upcoming rounds of events. Remember, the results are entered by a human so please be patient if you do not see your results immediately.\r\n\r\nQ: Are there age divisions?\r\nA: Nope! All competitors compete together.\r\n\r\nQ: I want to attend, or I have friends/family who want to attend, but not compete. Do they need to pay as well?\r\nA: No. All spectators are free to view the competition at no cost. There is payment only to compete. But in some cases, venue will be having restriction to allow spectators depending on the competition.\r\n\r\nQ: Can I have fun at this event?\r\nA: HECK YES! Cubing is amazing, and we sincerely hope you enjoy the competition!\r\n\r\nIf you have any further queries, please do mail the organizers & delegates.',1,'New Competitor Information'),
(13178,'2FeetofSnowinMontreal2019','**[FR]**\r\nEn transport en commun: [Mtro](http://www.stm.info/fr): Sortir  la station Beaudry. Marcher sur la rue Sainte-Catherine E (en direction du Starbucks), puis tourner  droite sur la rue Panet. La destination se trouve  droite. Voir [la carte](https://goo.gl/maps/Hy54un7TXU1JTTW98).\r\n\r\nEn auto: [Lien Google Maps](https://www.google.com/maps/dir//Centre+St-Pierre,+1212+Rue+Panet,+Montr%C3%A9al,+QC+H2L+2Y7/@45.5190166,-73.5880353,13z/data=!4m13!4m12!1m0!1m5!1m1!1s0x4cc91bae66054961:0x95b7cf45ba71d84f!2m2!1d-73.553016!2d45.519022!2m3!6e1!7e2!8j1577001600!3e0).\r\n* De l\'autoroute 720 Est, prendre la sortie 7, tourner immdiatement  gauche sur la rue Panet et encore  gauche sur l\'autoroute 720 Ouest. Suivre les indications ci-dessous...\r\n* De l\'autoroute 720 Ouest, prendre la sortie Viger (avant le tunnel Ville-Marie) et tourner immdiatement  droite sur la rue Wolfe puis encore  droite sur le boul. Ren-Lvesque. Enfin, face  la tour de Radio-Canada, tourner  gauche sur la rue Panet. \r\n* La rue Panet est un sens unique en direction Nord, alors il faut la prendre  partir de Ren-Lvesque.\r\n\r\n**Stationnement**: Il y a un stationnement au Centre St-Pierre qui est payant pour la journe (15 $ / jour). Il est parfois possible de trouver des places dans la rue  proximit mais il s\'agit d\'un coup de ds. Vous pouvez galement consulter [ce lien](https://en.parkopedia.ca/parking/locations/1212_rue_panet_montreal_quebec_h2l_2y6_canada_f25dynxbr8n/?country=ca&arriving=201912220800&leaving=201912221600) pour d\'autres options de stationnement  proximit  moindre cot. \r\nLa tarification des parcomtre est  3,25 $ / h et est en vigueur de 13 h 00  18 h 00 le dimanche [voyez la carte des parcomtres  proximit et le site web Stationnement de Montral](http://www.statdemtl.qc.ca/fr/).\r\n\r\n\r\n**[EN]**\r\nPublic transport: [Metro](http://www.stm.info/fr): Exit the metro at Beaudry station. Walk on Sainte-Catherine E street (towards the Starbucks), then turn right on Panet street. The center will be on the right. See [the map](https://goo.gl/maps/Hy54un7TXU1JTTW98).\r\n\r\nCar: [Google Maps link](https://www.google.com/maps/dir//Centre+St-Pierre,+1212+Rue+Panet,+Montr%C3%A9al,+QC+H2L+2Y7/@45.5190166,-73.5880353,13z/data=!4m13!4m12!1m0!1m5!1m1!1s0x4cc91bae66054961:0x95b7cf45ba71d84f!2m2!1d-73.553016!2d45.519022!2m3!6e1!7e2!8j1577001600!3e0).\r\n* From Highway 720 E, take exit 7, immediately turn left on Panet street then left again on Highway 720 W. Follow the directions under...\r\n* From Highway 720 W, take exit Viger (before the Ville-Marie tunnel) then immediately turn right on Wolfe street and right again on Ren-Lvesque boulevard. Once you have arrived in front of the Radio-Canada tower, turn left on Panet street. \r\n* Panet street is a one-way in the North direction, so one has to take it from Ren-Lvesque boulevard.\r\n\r\n**Parking**: There is parking available at the Centre St-Pierre for 15 $ / day. It is sometimes possible to find parking spots in the nearby streets but this is somewhat of a gamble. You can also take a look at [this link](https://en.parkopedia.ca/parking/locations/1212_rue_panet_montreal_quebec_h2l_2y6_canada_f25dynxbr8n/?country=ca&arriving=201912220800&leaving=201912221600) for cheaper parking options nearby.\r\nParking meters cost 3,25 $ / h from 13 h 00 to 18 h 00 on Sunday [see the map fo the parking meters nearby and the website Stationnement de Montral](http://www.statdemtl.qc.ca/fr/).\r\n',1,'Transport | Travel'),
(13179,'2FeetofSnowinMontreal2019','**[FR]**\r\n[Rsultats en direct](https://live.worldcubeassociation.org/competitions/2FeetofSnowinMontreal2019).\r\n\r\n**[EN]**\r\n[Live results](https://live.worldcubeassociation.org/competitions/2FeetofSnowinMontreal2019).',2,'Rsultats en direct | Live results'),
(13180,'2FeetofSnowinMontreal2019','**[FR]**\r\nBienvenue!\r\nSi ce sera votre premire comptition, voici ce que vous devez savoir :\r\n\r\n1. Vous devez vous [inscrire](https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/users/sign_up) ou vous [connecter](https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/users/sign_in) sur le site de la WCA.\r\n2. Vous devez vous inscrire  la comptition (sur la page de la comptition, onglet \"S\'inscrire\") et payer les frais d\'inscription.\r\n3. Il est indispensable de lire le [rglement WCA](https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/regulations/) (la traduction franaise est [ici](https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/regulations/translations/french/)).\r\n4. Nous vous invitons fortement  assister au \"Tutoriel nouveaux comptiteurs\".\r\n5. Vous devez **apporter une pice d\'identit** le jour de la comptition ou nous la numriser et l\'envoyer par courriel avant la comptition.\r\n\r\ngalement, nous vous recommandons de lire les [tutoriels de comptition](https://www.speedcubingfrance.org/speedcubing/tutos) de l\'AFS.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n**[EN]**\r\nWelcome!\r\nIf it\'s gonna be your first competition, here\'s what you need to know:\r\n\r\n1. You must [register](https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/users/sign_up) or [login](https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/users/sign_in) on the WCA website.\r\n2. You must register to the competition (tab \"Register\" on the competition page) and pay the registration fee.\r\n3. You must read the [WCA regulations](https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/regulations/) (translations are [here](https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/regulations/translations/)).\r\n4. We strongly advise you to come see the \"Tutorial for new competitors\".\r\n5. You must **bring an identification paper (ID, passport, driving license)** the day of the competition or scan and send it by email before the competition.\r\n\r\nWe also recommend you read the following [competition tutorial](https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/files/WCA_Competition_Tutorial.pdf).\r\n',3,'Nouveaux comptiteurs | New competitors'),
(13181,'2FeetofSnowinMontreal2019','**[FR]**\r\n**Stationnement**: Il y a un stationnement au Centre St-Pierre qui est payant pour la journe (15 $ / jour). Il est parfois possible de trouver des places dans la rue  proximit mais il s\'agit d\'un coup de ds. Vous pouvez galement consulter [ce lien](https://en.parkopedia.ca/parking/locations/1212_rue_panet_montreal_quebec_h2l_2y6_canada_f25dynxbr8n/?country=ca&arriving=201912220800&leaving=201912221600) pour d\'autres options de stationnement  proximit  moindre cot. \r\nLa tarification des parcomtre est  3,25 $ / h et est en vigueur de 13 h 00  18 h 00 le dimanche [voyez la carte des parcomtres  proximit et le site web Stationnement de Montral](http://www.statdemtl.qc.ca/fr/).\r\nTous les spectateurs sont les bienvenus!\r\n\r\n**[EN]**\r\n**Parking**: There is parking available at the Centre St-Pierre for 15 $ / day. It is sometimes possible to find parking spots in the nearby streets but this is somewhat of a gamble. You can also take a look at [this link](https://en.parkopedia.ca/parking/locations/1212_rue_panet_montreal_quebec_h2l_2y6_canada_f25dynxbr8n/?country=ca&arriving=201912220800&leaving=201912221600) for cheaper parking options nearby.\r\nParking meters cost 3,25 $ / h from 13 h 00 to 18 h 00 on Sunday [see the map fo the parking meters nearby and the website Stationnement de Montral](http://www.statdemtl.qc.ca/fr/).\r\nAll spectators are welcome!\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n',4,'Infos supplmentaires | Additional Info'),
(13184,'2FeetofSnowinMontreal2019','**[FR]**\r\nIl y a plusieurs restaurants  environ 5 minutes de marche du site de la comptition. Des micro-ondes sont disponibles sur place si vous dsirez amener un repas chaud.\r\n\r\n**[EN]**\r\nThere are several restaurants within a 5 minutes walk from the competition venue. Microwave ovens are also available for use on site.',5,'Nourriture | Food'),
