(17774,'1stSriLankanOpen2022','Following meals are available free of charge for all the registered competitors\r\n* Morning Snacks\r\n* Lunch\r\n* Evening Snacks\r\n\r\nGuests/spectators can buy meal tokens for LKR 1,500 from the entrance, if required.',2,'Meals'),
(18962,'333OnlyHamiltonA2022','**By registering for this competition you agree that you and (if applicable) your guest understand and will follow the following policies:**\r\n\r\n1. **Masks are to be required at all times, and must cover your nose and mouth.** If you refuse to wear a mask inside of the venue, you will be disqualified from the competition and be asked to leave the premises. *There will be no exceptions to this policy.* Please consume all food and drink outside of the venue.\r\n\r\n2. Competitors should not attend the competition if they test positive for COVID-19, if they are experiencing symptoms of COVID-19, or if they were in close contact to someone who tested positive for COVID-19. If this occurs to you, please [email the organizers](mailto:hamilton2022@speedcubingcanada.org) and we will arrange a full refund of your registration fee.\r\n\r\n3. **Competitors may bring at most one (1) guest.** Competitors over the age of 18 are encouraged to come without a guest.\r\n\r\n4. Whenever possible, competitors and guests are encouraged to socially distance from others.\r\n\r\nThese policies are subject to change as deemed necessary by the organizers, the WCA Board, or municipal/provincial/federal government.\r\n',1,'COVID-19 Safety Policy'),
(19376,'1stSalemOpen2022','For those of you new to cubing, WELCOME!\r\n\r\nWe wanted to let you know this event is perfectly fine for cubers of ANY age and experience. We just ask you know a couple things before coming to compete...\r\n\r\nFirst, please be familiar with the WCA Regulations, found here:\r\nhttps://www.worldcubeassociation.org/regulations/\r\n\r\nThis video will explain most of what any cuber competing for the first time will need to know.\r\n\r\nyoutube(https://www.youtube.com/embed/dPL3eV-A0ww)\r\n\r\nIf you are stoked to compete and ready to sign up, head over to the \'Registration & Payment\' tab and it will guide you to the registration.\r\n\r\n**FAQs**\r\n\r\nQ: Do I use my own cube to compete?\r\nA: YES! You are responsible for your own hardware in order to compete. This means you should bring your own cube.\r\n\r\nQ: What is the normal age of competitors at these events?\r\nA: All ages are welcome, but in general competitors are between 10 and 20 years old. Don\'t let this stop you though, everyone can and should cube!\r\n\r\nQ: How do I find results?\r\nA: All results are posted on the WCA page within a week after the competition finishes. However, for the day of competing, go to Cubecomps.com to find information about current events. This is also where you will find information about upcoming rounds of events. Remember, the results are entered by a human so please be patient if you do not see your results immediately.\r\n\r\nQ: Are there age divisions?\r\nA: Nope! All competitors compete together.\r\n\r\nQ: I want to attend, or I have friends/family who want to attend, but not compete. Do they need to pay as well?\r\nA: No. All spectators are free to view the competition at no cost. There is payment only to compete. But in some cases, venue will be having restriction to allow spectators depending on the competition.\r\n\r\nQ: Can I have fun at this event?\r\nA: HECK YES! Cubing is amazing, and we sincerely hope you enjoy the competition!\r\n\r\nIf you have any further queries, please do mail the organizers & delegates.',1,'New Competitor Information'),
(22563,'2x2inaMadisonLodge2022','For those of you new to cubing, WELCOME!\r\n\r\nWe wanted to let you know this event is perfectly fine for cubers of any age and experience. We just ask you know a couple things before coming to compete...\r\n\r\nIf you are stoked to compete and ready to sign up, head over to the registration tab, click register, and fill out the information it asks for. This will help you get set up the WCA\'s system and one step closer to your first official solve!\r\n\r\nQ&A:\r\n\r\nQ: Do I use my own cube to compete?\r\n\r\nA: YES! You are responsible for your own hardware in order to compete.\r\n\r\nQ: What is the normal age of competitors at these events?\r\n\r\nA: All ages are welcome, but in general competitors are between 10 and 20 years old. Don\'t let this stop you though, everyone can and should cube!\r\n\r\nQ: What is the competition like?\r\n\r\nA: Competitions are a bunch of tables where nerds like us get to sit and discuss our favorite thing, Cubes! Of course in addition there is competing, which will occupy one side of the pavilion, where you will see lots of timers flickering with contestants new personal bests.\r\n\r\nQ: When do I need to show up?\r\n\r\nA: Look at the schedule on the competition website. You must be present and ready to compete during all events that you are registered for. The schedule is subject to change. We recommend coming about 15-30 minutes before the start of your first event.\r\n\r\nQ: How do I find results?\r\n\r\nA: All results are posted on the WCA page a couple of days after the competition finishes. However, for the day of competing, go to live.worldcubeassociation.org to find information about current events. This is also where you will find information about 2nd and 3rd rounds of events.\r\n\r\nQ: Why am I not on the registration list yet?\r\n\r\nA: Make sure you pay you entrance fee in order to be automatically placed on the registered list, which will also guarantee you a spot in the competition.\r\n\r\nQ: Are there age divisions?\r\n\r\nA: Nope! All competitors compete in the same group.\r\n\r\nQ: Do spectators have to pay to attend?\r\n\r\nA: No\r\n\r\nQ: Can you add more events?\r\nA: No.\r\n\r\nQ: Can I have fun at this event?\r\n\r\nA: HECK YES! Cubing is amazing, and we sincerely hope you enjoy the competition!',2,'FAQ'),
(22564,'2x2inaMadisonLodge2022','-Before the competition, watch [this great video](https://youtu.be/dPL3eV-A0ww) made by Former WCA Senior Delegate Kit Clement with the basics of how it all works.\r\n-There is also [this written tutorial](https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/edudoc/competitor-tutorial/tutorial.pdf) on the WCA website that is very helpful.\r\n-The competitors will be split up into groups for competing. You will be assigned a group, which you can find on the Groups Tab.\r\n-On the day of the competition when your group number is called you bring your puzzle up and put it in the box that has a scorecard with your name on it and wait in the competitor waiting area until your name is called.\r\n-It\'s a good idea to arrive before the scheduled time for your event because if you are not there for the last call you might not be allowed to compete.',3,'New Competitor Information'),
(22980,'2x2inaMadisonLodge2022','You can apply for staff [here](https://forms.gle/pwkPin6gXSSaBpfEA):\r\n\r\nStaff members are expected to be helping out for most of the groups that they are not competing in themselves.\r\n\r\nStaff benefits (contingent on the competition filling):\r\n- Lunch provided for staff members on days they are staffing\r\n- Partial registration fee refund ($10)\r\n\r\nIf you do not fill out this form, you will NOT be eligible for these benefits regardless of how much you help out during the competition. Please fill out this form if you would like to staff. We will let you know whether or not you have been accepted closer to the competition date.',4,'Staff'),
(22981,'2x2inaMadisonLodge2022','By registering for this competition, you agree that you understand all the information presented in this tab, will abide by all the COVID-19 restrictions placed on this competition, and acknowledge the risk of contracting COVID-19 or any other disease in attending an event of this scale.\r\n\r\nMasks are OPTIONAL at this competition\r\nIf you have symptoms related to COVID-19 such as cough, fever, shortness of breath, etc. do not attend this competition.\r\nIf you have had a positive COVID-19 test or prolonged exposure to someone with the virus within 7 days prior to the competition, do not attend.\r\nThe competition may be cancelled if the COVID-19 situation in Wisconsin and/or the US gets worse.\r\nNote: The COVID safety restrictions may change if cases increase or decrease in Wisconsin and/or the US.',1,'COVID Precautions'),
(23644,'2x2inaMadisonLodge2022','This competition is sponsored by [TheCubicle](https://www.thecubicle.com/)! They will provide gift card codes to the podium winners! \r\n\r\n![](https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/redirect/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBblVlIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--0e4fb93e14fae783ae7f68bb5b25ade2f1644c5d/theCubicle.com.png)\r\n',5,'Sponsor'),
(23998,'2x2inaMadisonLodge2022','You can find your groups for this competition at this link: https://www.competitiongroups.com/competitions/2x2inaMadisonLodge2022\r\n\r\nLive results during the competition can be found here: https://live.worldcubeassociation.org/competitions/1790',6,'Groups/Live Results'),
(29072,'24HoursinFlen2023','### Svenska\r\n#### Koncept\r\nDenna tvling kommer pg frn lrdag 13:45 till sndag 14:45, med omgngar under hela natten.\r\nOmgngarna och deras tidstgng r frutbestmda, men ordningen kommer avgras av slumpen under tvlingen. Efter varje omgng snurras ett hjul som avgr vad nsta omgng blir. Detta pgr under hela tvlingen tills omgngarna r slut och 24 timmar har uppntts. Sjlvklart kommer eventuella finalrundor dock inte kunna hllas innan den frsta rundan i samma gren r genomfrd.\r\n\r\n**Obs:** Vnligen notera att detta r en mycket speciell tvling med helt andra frutsttningar r vanligt. Det kommer innebra en stor pfrestning, och vi rekommenderar att tnka efter om du kommer ha mjlighet att genomfra tvlingen. Tvlingen rekommenderas varken fr yngre barn eller fr helt nya deltagare.\r\n\r\nEn sngplats i vandrarhemsstandard samt frukost ingr fr alla godknda deltagare, och finns i samma hus som sjlva tvlingen, mer information finns under fliken [boende](https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/competitions/24HoursinFlen2023#29076-boende-accomodation).\r\n\r\nTre stycken matpauser finns inlagda i schemat, hr passar det bra att ta medhavd mat eller ta lite frisk luft. Ett fullt utrustat kk finns i samma rum som tvlingen genomfrs (kyl, frys, ugn, spis, micro osv).\r\n\r\n#### 24 timmar 3BLD (+ eventuella andra inofficiella sidogrenar)\r\nUtver de vanliga omgngarna kommer en specialgren ordnas, en 3BLD-lsning som strcker sig ver 24 timmar. Alla som vill delta fr vid incheckningen memorera en 3x3, sedan dljs kuben tills slutet av tvlingen, d man lser den med gonbindel. Tiden mts fr bde memoreringen p lrdagen och exekveringen p sndagen. Mellan memorering och lsning fr inga fysiska noteringar gras, precis som under vanlig blindlsning. Det r allts exempelvis inte tilltet att skriva ner sin memorering, eller gra den baklnges p en annan kub fr att kunna \"va\" p sin lsning.\r\n\r\nDet kan hnda att det blir andra inofficiella sidogrenar ocks, lite beroende p hur vi ligger till i schemat samt hur mnga officiella rundor vi har kvar nr dygnet brjar n sitt slut. Eventuella sdana inofficiella grenar annonseras p plats i lokalen.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n### English\r\n#### Concept\r\nThis competition will run from Saturday 1:45pm to Sunday 2:45pm, with rounds throughout the night.\r\nThe rounds and their durations are predetermined, but the order will be determined by chance during the competition. After each round, a wheel is spun which determines what the next round will be. This goes on throughout the competition until the rounds are over and 24 hours have passed. Of course, any final rounds will not be held before the first round in the same event has been completed.\r\n\r\n**Note:** Please note that this is a very special competition with completely different conditions than usual. It will be very tiring, and we recommend thinking about whether you will actually be able to complete the competition. The competition is not recommended for younger children or for completely new participants.\r\n\r\nA bed in hostel standard and breakfast is included for all approved registrants, and is in the same building as the competition itself, more information is available in the tab [accommodation](https://www.worldcubeasociation.org/competitions/24HoursinFlen2023#29076-boende-accomodation) .\r\n\r\nThree meal breaks are included in the schedule, which serves as good oppurtunities to eat any food you brought or get some fresh air. A fully equipped kitchen is found in the same room as the competition (fridge, freezer, oven, stove, microwave, etc.).\r\n\r\n#### 24 hours 3BLD (+ potential other unofficial side events)\r\nIn addition to the regular rounds, a special event will be organized, a 3BLD solve that spans 24 hours. Everyone who wishes to take part memorizes a 3x3 at check-in, then the cube is hidden until the end of the competition, when it is solved blindfolded. The time is measured for both the memorization on Saturday and the execution on Sunday. Between memorizing and solving it is not permitted to make physical notes, just like in normal blindfolded solving. This means you are not allowed to for example write down your memo, or execute it backwards on another cube to \"practice\" your solution.\r\n\r\nIt may happen that there will be other unofficial side events as well, depending on how well we adhere to the schedule and how many official rounds we have left when the competition starts to come to an end. Any such unofficial events will be announced on site.',1,'Koncept'),
(29073,'24HoursinFlen2023','## SveKub\r\n\r\nDenna tvling arrangeras tillsammans med SveKub.\r\n\r\nSom medlem i SveKub har du alltid 25% rabatt p tvlingar, och medlemskapet r **gratis**!\r\nLs mer om att bli medlem [p vr hemsida](https://svekub.se/bli-medlem/) eller [registrera dig direkt](https://ebas.sverok.se/blimedlem/SveKub).\r\n\r\nFr att ta del av rabatten r det bara att vara registrerad i SveKubs medlemsregister, sedan anmler du dig som vanligt.\r\nAlla betalar fullt pris till att brja med, och vi betalar tillbaka 25% till de som r medlemmar. Vi verifierar medlemskapet och terbetalar rabatten vid tv tillfllen, en gng 24 timmar efter att anmlan ppnat, och en gng nr anmlan stngt.\r\nI framtiden hoppas vi kunna ha ett ngot smidigare system, men anmlningssystemet kan i dagslget inte ha olika anmlningsavgifter fr olika personer.\r\n\r\n#### Vill du ocks arrangera en tvling?\r\n**Du kan ocks arrangera en tvling i din stad!** Det enda kravet r att du har koll p en lokal som hade passat bra fr en tvling. Det kan vara allt frn matsalar, gymnastiksalar, bygdegrdar, folkets hus och klubb- eller samlingslokaler. Sjlva tvlingen kan pg i bara ett par timmar p en vardagskvll eller en hel lnghelg, du bestmmer. Drefter kan SveKub hjlpa till med det du inte kan eller vill gra sjlv, ssom tvlingsschema, budget och hemsida. Mer information om och hur det gr till att arrangera en tvling finns [hr](https://svekub.se/arrangera/).\r\n\r\n--\r\n\r\n## SveKub\r\n\r\nThis competition is organized together with SveKub.\r\n\r\nAs a member of SveKub, you always have a 25% discount on competitions. The membership is free, but is only available for Swedish citizens.\r\nRead more about becoming a member [on our website](https://svekub.se/en/bli-medlem/) or [register right away](https://ebas.sverok.se/blimedlem/SveKub).\r\n\r\nTo get the discount, you simply need to be registered as a SveKub member. After that, you register as normal and we will verify which competitors are members and which are not.\r\nEveryone pays full price at first, and we will then refund 25% to members. We verify the membership and refund the discount at two occasions, once 24 hours after registration opens, and once when registration has closed.\r\nIn the future, we hope to have a slightly more convenient system, but the current registration system can not have different registration fees for different people.\r\n\r\n#### Do you also want to organize a competition?\r\n**You can also organize a competition in your city!** The only requirement is that you know a venue that would be suitable for a competition. It can be anything from canteens, sport halls, community centers and club or meeting rooms. You decide for how long the competition should run, anything from a couple of hours on a weekday to an entire weekend is a possibility. After that, SveKub can help with what you can\'t or don\'t want to do yourself, such as a competition schedule, budget and website. More information about and how to organize a competition is available [here](https://svekub.se/arrangera/).',2,'SveKub'),
(29074,'24HoursinFlen2023','### Viktig info\r\n\r\n**Alla tvande ska ha lst [WCA:s Regler](https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/regulations/).** Deltagare frvntas knna till WCA:s reglemente innan man deltar p en officiell tvling. Reglerna finns ven versatta till [svenska](https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/regulations/translations/swedish/), men tnk p att det r den engleska originalversionen som gller om det skulle finnas ngra skillnader.\r\n\r\nVi kommer ha en deltagarintroduktion p lrdag morgon fr nya deltagare dr vi gr igenom hur det gr till nr man tvlar p en officiell WCA-tvling. Vill man redan nu f bttre koll p hur tvlingsproceduren gr till, kolla d grna [denna video](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LUU7YKnSn1g) som visar detta p ett bra stt. Att lsa igenom [denna guide](https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/edudoc/competitor-tutorial/se/tutorial.pdf) r ocks en bra id eftersom den visar det mesta man behver knna till som deltagare.\r\n\r\n**Du mste vara anmld till tvlingen online fr att f tvla!** Du kan anmla dig [hr](https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/competitions/24HoursinFlen2023/register).\r\n\r\n**Alla nya tvlande br ha med ett giltigt ID.** Fr att f tvla som ny deltagare mste du kunna identifiera dig sjlv och visa att den information du gav oss nr du registrerade dig fr den hr tvlingen r korrekt. Ett pass r ett bra exempel p ett giltigt ID eftersom det visar all ndvndig information, ssom namn, nationalitet och fdelsedatum. Om den tvlande r ung och inte har ett eget ID kan en vrdnadshavare verifiera att uppgifterna stmmer.\r\n\r\n**Fotografering med blixt r frbjudet i hela lokalen!** Blixtar r strande fr tvlande. Fotografering utan blixt r tilltet.\r\n\r\n**Publik mste befinna sig 1,5 meter ifrn tvlingsstationerna och tvlingsomrdet** Annars finns risken att man str andra tvlande eller tvlingsproceduren.\r\n\r\n**Man fr inte prata om blandningarna innan man tvlat frdigt i pgende gren** Annars finns risken att man blir diskvalificerad.\r\n\r\n**Hll koll p er e-mail** Ngra dagar innan tvlingen kommer ni f ett deltagarmail dr vi kommer ta upp diverse viktig information fr deltagare att knna till. I detta mail kommer ocks eventuella ndringar sedan tvlingen annonserades tas upp. Om det finns annan information som vi snabbt mste kommunicera till deltagare s kommer detta ocks ske via e-mail, drfr r det viktigt att ni hller koll p er e-mail regelbundet.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n### Important info\r\n\r\n**All competitors must have read the [WCA regulations](https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/regulations/).** Participants are expected to know WCA\'s regulations before attending an official competition. \r\n\r\nWe will have a competitor tutorial for new participants on Saturday morning, where we will show how to compete in an official WCA competition. If you want to get a better idea of how the competition works already, please check [this video](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dPL3eV-A0ww) which will show you this. Reading through [this guide](https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/edudoc/competitor-tutorial/tutorial.pdf). is also a good idea since it shows most things a competitor needs to know.\r\n\r\n**You must be registered for this competetiton online in order to compete!** You can register [here](https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/competitions/24HoursinFlen2023/register).\r\n\r\n**All new competitors should bring a valid ID.** To be allowed to compete as a new competitor, you need to be able to identify yourself and the information you provided us when you registred for this competition. A passport is a good example of a valid ID since it shows all necessary information, such as name, nationality and date of birth. If the competitor is young and does not have an ID, a parent or guardian can confirm that the information is correct instead.\r\n\r\n**No flash photography in the entire venue!** Flash is distracting to the competitors. Pictures without the use of flash are allowed.\r\n\r\n**Spectators should remain 1,5 meters away from the solving stations and the competition area.** Otherwise, you might distract other competitors or disrupt the competition flow.\r\n\r\n**You are not allowed to talk about the scrambles until the round is done** Otherwise, you might get disqualified.\r\n\r\n**Check your e-mail** A few days before the competition, you will receive a participant email where we will address various important information for participants to know. This email will also include any changes made since the competition was announced. If there is any other urgent information which we need to communicate to competitors, then it will be done through e-mail so therefore it is important that you check your e-mail regularly.',3,'Viktig Info / Important Info'),
(29075,'24HoursinFlen2023','### Nya tvlande\r\n\r\nOm det hr r din frsta WCA-tvling, vlkommen! Det r viktigt att du lser igenom alla flikar hr p sidan, eftersom det finns mycket viktig information dr. Notera dock ocks att denna tvling har ett synnerligen koncept, som antagligen inte passar varken nya eller yngre deltagare srskilt bra. Det arrangeras dock mnga [andra vanliga tvlingar runt om i Sverige varje mnad](https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/competitions?region=Sweden&search=&state=present&year=all+years&from_date=&to_date=&delegate=&display=list), och antagligen kan ngon av dessa passa bttre.\r\n\r\nOm du aldrig tvlat frut br du ha med ett giltigt ID, till exempel ett pass eller krkort, fr att intyga nr du r fdd och din nationalitet. Om den tvlande inte har ett ID kan en frlder bekrfta dessa uppgifter.\r\n\r\nVi rekommenderar starkt att du ven kollar p [den hr videon](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LUU7YKnSn1g) s du bttre frstr hur det gr till att lsa i tvling. Att lsa igenom  [denna guide](https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/edudoc/competitor-tutorial/se/tutorial.pdf) r ocks en bra id eftersom den visar det mesta man behver knna till som deltagare. \r\n\r\nDet r ocks viktigt att du lser igenom [WCA-reglerna](https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/regulations/) s du fr en bttre frstelse fr vilka olika tidsstraff du kan f p lsningarna, och hur du undviker dem. \r\n\r\nUnder hela tvlingen kommer du kunna se live-resultat frn [WCA Live](https://live.worldcubeassociation.org/), dr kan du se vilka resultat du fick, och ifall du gick vidare till nsta runda.\r\n\r\nOm du har ngra frgor, maila grna ngon av arrangrerna, vi hjlper dig grna!\r\n\r\n-----\r\n\r\n### New competitors\r\n\r\nIf this is your first WCA competition, welcome! Make sure to read through all tabs above as there is a lot of important information there. However, also note that this competition has a special concept, which probably does not suit neither new or younger participants very well. However, many [other regular competitions are held around Sweden every month](https://www.worldcubeasociation.org/competitions?region=Sweden&search=&state=present&year=all+years&from_date=&to_date=&delegate=&display=list), and probably one of these might be a better fit.\r\n\r\nIf you\'ve never competed before, you should bring a valid ID, for example a passport or driver\'s licence, to verify your birth date and nationality. If the competitor does not have an ID, a parent can confirm this information.\r\n\r\nWe highly recommend watching [this video](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dPL3eV-A0ww) to get a good understanding of how solving in competition works. Reading through  [this guide](https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/edudoc/competitor-tutorial/tutorial.pdf) is also a good idea since it shows most things a competitor needs to know.\r\n\r\nIt is also important that you read through the [WCA Regulations](https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/regulations/) so that you are aware of different penalties and how to avoid them.\r\n\r\nThroughout the competition, you will be able to see live results from [WCA Live](https://live.worldcubeassociation.org/), and there you can see what results you got and whether or not you proceeded to the next round. \r\n\r\nIf you have any questions, feel free to email one of the organizers, we\'re happy to help!',4,'Nya Tvlande / New Competitors'),
(29076,'24HoursinFlen2023','### Boende - Gula Lngan (vandrarhemsstandard)\r\nTvlingen genomfrs i det allrum som tillhr lgergrden Gula Lngan. En sngplats fr natten inklusive frukost ingr i anmlningsavgiften fr alla anmlda deltagare. Den deltagare som har en godknd anmlan behver allts inte fylla i nedanstende formulr, eller betala extra. Glm ej att ta med lakan, pslakan och rngott.\r\n\r\nNotera att tvlingen kommer pg hela natten, s om man vill sova kommer man missa ngra av tvlingsomgngarna. Eftersom ordningen slumpas fram lpande gr det inte heller att veta vilka omgngar man i s fall kommer missa.\r\n\r\nEventuella gster och frldrar kan boka extra sngplats genom att fylla i detta [formulr](https://forms.gle/7t1wqTZXop7kyAPq6). Kom ihg att betalningen p 300kr per person och natt mste betalas innan bokningen r slutfrd. Enklast r att betala genom Swish till SveKub: 123 688 29 97. Om betalning via Swish inte r mjligt gr det ven att betala fr bokningen genom en \"donation\" under den ordinarie registreringsprocessen till sjlva tvlingen. Om inte heller detta gr s kan tvlingsarrangren kontaktas fr att finna en alternativ lsning.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n### Accommodation - Gula Lngan (hostel standard)\r\nThe competition is held in the common room belonging to the Gula Lngan camp. A bed for the night including breakfast is included in the registration fee for all registered competitors. Any competitor who has an approved registration therefore does not need to fill in the form below, or pay extra. Don\'t forget to bring sheets, duvet covers and pillowcases.\r\n\r\nNote that the competition will be running trough the night, so if you want to sleep, you will miss some of the rounds. Since the order is randomized, it is not possible to know which rounds you will miss.\r\n\r\nGuests or parents can book an extra bed by filling out this [form](https://forms.gle/7t1wqTZXop7kyAPq6). Remember that you must pay the fee of 300 SEK per person and night before your booking is confirmed. The easiest way to pay is through Swish to SveKub: 123 688 29 97. If a payment through Swish is not possible (e.g. foreigners), it is also possible to pay through the \"donation\" field during the normal registration process to the competition. If also this is not possible, please contact the organizer to find another solution.',5,'Boende / Accomodation'),
(29077,'24HoursinFlen2023','### Resa\r\n#### Med bil: \r\nAdressen till tvlingslokalen r [Hammarvallen 3, Flen](https://www.google.se/maps/place/Flens+If/@59.056063,16.571624,18.91z/data=!4m6!3m5!1s0x465ec4a05d995167:0x22f261871c659b69!8m2!3d59.0560702!4d16.5713907!16s%2Fg%2F1hc0z2svn). Gott om gratis parkering finns framfr lokalen. Vi vill dock utfrda en pminnelse om att tvlingen pgr nonstop i 24 timmar, och att ingen mnniska som tvlat hela natten r en srskilt lmplig bilfrare efter det. Fundera grna p om det gr att ka kollektivt istllet.\r\n\r\n#### Med tg:\r\nTa tget till Flens station. Tvlingslokalen r 900 meters gngvg frn stationen. Biljetter kan bokas via [sj.se](https://www.sj.se), men om din resa endast inkluderar Mlartg s r det billigare att boka sin biljett p [malartag.se](www.malartag.se), eller via deras app.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n### Travel\r\n#### By car\r\nThe address to the venue is [Hammarvallen 3, Flen](https://www.google.se/maps/place/Flens+If/@59.056063,16.571624,18.91z/data=!4m6!3m5!1s0x465ec4a05d995167:0x22f261871c659b69!8m2!3d59.0560702!4d16.5713907!16s%2Fg%2F1hc0z2svn). There is lots of parking available right in front of the venue. However, we would like to issue a reminder that the competition runs non-stop for 24 hours, and no one who has competed all night is a particularly fit driver after that. Feel free to consider whether it is possible to travel by public transport instead.\r\n\r\n#### By train\r\nThe competition schedule has been adjusted to fit the train timetable, mainly from Stockholm but also from Gothenburg, Malm / Copenhagen and other destinations. Take the train to Flen\'s train station. The venue is located 700 meters away from the station on foot. Train tickets can be booked through [sj.se](https://www.sj.se), but if your journey only involves \"Mlartg\", then it is cheaper to book through [malartag.se](www.malartag.se), or through their app. ',6,'Resa / Travel'),
(29078,'24HoursinFlen2023','### Mat\r\nMnga mataffrer ligger nra tvlingslokalen, i Flens centrum. En pizzeria och ngra restauranger ligger ocks i centrum, cirka 900 meter frn lokalen. Frukost ingr i anmlningsavgiften och kommer serveras i allrummet. \r\n\r\nTre stycken matpauser finns inlagda i schemat, hr passar det bra att ta medhavd mat eller ta lite frisk luft. Ett fullt utrustat kk finns i samma rum som tvlingen genomfrs (kyl, frys, ugn, spis, micro osv).\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n### Food\r\nMany supermarkets are located close to the venue, in the city center. A pizzeria and a few restaurants are also located at the city center, about 900 meters away from the venue. Breakfast is included in the registration fee and will be served in the common room.\r\n\r\nThree meal breaks are included in the schedule, which serves as good oppurtunities to eat any food you brought or get some fresh air. A fully equipped kitchen is found in the same room as the competition (fridge, freezer, oven, stove, microwave, etc.).',7,'Mat / Food'),
(29079,'24HoursinFlen2023','## Liveresultat\r\nUnder tvlingen kan ni se liveresultat p [WCA Live](https://live.worldcubeassociation.org).\r\nDet r ocks dr du kan se dina egna tider och om du gick vidare till nsta omgng eller inte. \r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Live Results\r\nDuring the competition you can see live results on [WCA Live](https://live.worldcubeassociation.org).\r\nThat is also where you can see your own times and whether you advanced to the next round or not.',8,'Liveresultat / Live Results'),
(29080,'24HoursinFlen2023','[![](https://cuboss.se/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/logo_400.png)](https://cuboss.se/?r=wca)\r\n\r\n### Sponsor - Cuboss\r\n24 Hours in Flen 2023 sponsras av kub-butiken [Cuboss.se](https://cuboss.se/?r=wca)! Cuboss r en svensk onlinebutik specialiserad p speedcubes och andra typer av pussel, vilka de levererar bde inom Sverige samt till resten av vrlden. Cuboss har valt att sponsra tvlingen med presentkort till medaljrerna i de olika grenarna enligt nedan:\r\n\r\nMedaljrer i 3x3x3 tilldelas presentkort frn Cuboss enligt fljande:\r\n1:a plats: 100 kr\r\n\r\nDessutom kommer 1 presentkort p Cuboss vrt 100 kr att lottas ut till deltagare p prisceremonin, dr alla som nrvarar har chans att vinna ett!\r\n\r\n-----\r\n\r\n### Sponsor - Cuboss\r\n\r\n24 Hours in Flen 2023 is sponsored by the cube store [Cuboss.com](https://cuboss.com/?r=wca)! Cuboss is an online cube store based in Sweden, specializing in speedcubes and other types of puzzles, with worldwide delivery available. Cuboss has generously chosen to sponsor the competition with gift cards for the medalists in the various event as outlined below:\r\n\r\nMedalists in 3x3x3 are awarded gift cards from Cuboss as below:\r\n1st place: SEK 100\r\n\r\nIn addition, 1 gift card worth SEK 100 will be randomly drawn to competitors at the award ceremony, where everyone who attends has a chance to win one!',9,'Sponsorer & Priser / Sponsors & Prizes'),
(33824,'10AniversarioGuatemala2023','**PARQUEO:**\r\n\r\nHabr parqueo en el lugar.\r\n\r\n**RESULTADOS EN VIVO:**\r\n\r\nSe podr ver un preliminar de los resultados que se generen en la pgina WCA Live.\r\n\r\n**REGLAMENTO Y CUBOS PERMITIDOS:**\r\n\r\nTodos los competidores deben estar familiarizados con el [reglamento de la WCA](https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/regulations/translations/spanish-american/) \r\nPara tener una idea ms clara de cmo funcionan las competencias oficiales pueden ver este [video](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dPL3eV-A0ww) (disponible con subttulos en espaol)\r\nLos cubos son proporcionados por cada competidor, y cualquier cubo es vlido. Se prohiben nicamente los cubos que tengan rasgadas las calcomanas y los cubos cuyo plstico sea transparente o traslcido, en 3x3x3 a ciegas, no se pueden usar cubos que tengan algn tipo de logo, aunque sea impreso.\r\n\r\n\r\n**PARKING INFORMATION:**\r\n\r\nThere will be available parking space\r\n\r\n**LIVE RESULTS:**\r\n\r\nIt will be possible to check preliminary results generated by WCA Live website.\r\n\r\n**REGULATIONS AND ALLOWED PUZZLES:**\r\n\r\nAll competitors must be familiar with [WCA regulations](https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/regulations/translations/spanish-american/), you may watch this [video](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dPL3eV-A0ww) to have an idea of how official competitions work. Competitors must provide their own puzzles for competition.\r\n',1,'Informacin adicional'),
(33999,'100YearsRepublicIstanbul2023','[TR]\r\n\r\nOnline deme iin kayt cretleri.\r\n\r\nAna giri creti : 250 TL (3x3 kategorisi iin)\r\n2-3 kategori giri creti: 350 TL\r\n4-6 kategori giri creti: 400 TL\r\n7-10 kategori giri creti: 450 TL\r\n\r\nYarmada kayt iin kayt cretleri\r\n\r\nAna giri creti : 300 TL (3x3 kategorisi iin)\r\n2-3 kategori giri creti: 400 TL\r\n4-6 kategori giri creti: 450 TL\r\n7-10 kategori giri creti: 500 TL\r\n\r\nYarma creti iin i.kuleli@gmail.com adresine adnzla birlikte mail atn. Gerekli bilgiler mail ile ulatrlacaktr.\r\nYarmadan 1 hafta nce onay iin mail atlacaktr, ltfen maillerinizi kontrol edin.\r\n\r\nletiim iin: +90 507 587 33 76\r\n\r\n[EN]\r\n\r\nRegistration fee for online payment\r\n\r\nBase registration fee: 250 TL (3x3 category included)\r\n2-3 category registration fee: 350 TL\r\n4-6 category registration fee: 400 TL\r\n7-10 category registration fee: 450 TL\r\n\r\nRegistration fee for at the registration desk payment\r\n\r\nBase registration fee: 300 TL (3x3 category included)\r\n2-3 category registration fee: 400 TL\r\n4-6 category registration fee: 450 TL\r\n7-10 category registration fee: 500 TL\r\n\r\nFor the competition fee, send an e-mail to i.kuleli@gmail.com with your name. Necessary information will be sent by e-mail.\r\n1 week before the competition, an e-mail will be sent for confirmation, please check your e-mails.\r\n\r\nContact: +90 507 587 33 76',1,'Kayt creti / Registration Fee'),
