 [competitiongroups.com](https://www.competitiongroups.com/).** Everyone will not compete in the different events at the same time, instead they are divided into groups. On this page you can see which group you compete in for the events you are registered for. At larger competitions, for example, judge assignments are also predetermined for the slightly more experienced participants, and in these cases these are also published on the website above.\r\n\r\n**Check your e-mail** A few days before the competition, you might receive a participant email where we will address various important information for participants to know. This email will also include any changes made since the competition was announced. If there is any other urgent information which we need to communicate to competitors, then it will be done through e-mail so therefore it is important that you check your e-mail regularly.\r\n\r\nIf you have any questions, please email one of the organizers, we will be happy to help!',3,'Viktig information / Important information'),
(43625,'24HoursinAker2024','### Boende\r\nVi kommer hlla vervningen i tvlingslokalen ppen, och dr kan de som vill sova. Ta i s fall med allt du behver, exempelvis luftmadrass och sovsck.\r\n\r\nNotera dock att tvlingen kommer pg hela natten, s om man vill sova kommer man missa ngra av tvlingsomgngarna. Eftersom ordningen slumpas fram lpande gr det inte heller att veta vilka omgngar man i s fall kommer missa.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n### Accommodation\r\nWe will keep the second floor of the venue open, where anyone who wishes to sleep can do so. In that case, remember to bring all you need, for example and air matress and a sleeping bag.\r\n\r\nPlease note that the competition will be running trough the night, so if you want to sleep, you will miss some of the rounds. Since the order is randomized, it is not possible to know which rounds you will miss.\r\n\r\n',4,'Boende / Accomodation'),
(43626,'24HoursinAker2024','### Resa\r\n#### Med bil\r\nAdressen till lokalen r Torget 1, 647 52 kers Styckebruk.\r\nParkering finns i direkt anslutning till lokalen. **Vi vill dock utfrda en pminnelse om att tvlingen pgr nonstop i 24 timmar, och att ingen mnniska som tvlat hela natten r en srskilt lmplig bilfrare efter det. Fundera grna p om det gr att ka kollektivt istllet.**\r\n\r\n#### Med tg / buss\r\nTg till Lggesta tgstation som ligger ca 40 minuter frn Stockholm och 25 minuter frn Eskilstuna. Drefter buss 306 till kers Styckebruk busshllplats Stiftelsen eller Folkets Hus. Lnk till Srmlandstrafiken hittar du hr: [Srmlandstrafiken](https://sormlandstrafiken.se/)\r\n\r\nKom ihg att medlemmar i SveKub reser med upp till 10% rabatt hos SJ, mer information finns p Sveroks [hemsida](https://medlem.sverok.se/reserabatt/). Resor med alla Sveriges kollektivtrafikbolag kan skas via [Resrobot.se](https://resrobot.se/).\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n### Travel\r\n#### By car\r\nThe address to the venue is Torget 1, 647 52 kers Styckebruk.\r\nParking is available directly adjacent to the competition venue. **However, we would like to issue a reminder that the competition runs non-stop for 24 hours, and no one who has competed all night is a particularly fit driver after that. Please consider whether it is possible to travel by public transport instead.**\r\n\r\n#### By train / bus\r\nFirst, take a train to Lggesta train station, which is about 40 minutes from Stockholm and 25 minutes from Eskilstuna. Then, take Bus 306 to kers Styckebruk bus stop at Stiftelsen or Folkets Hus. Here is the link to Srmlandstrafiken\'s website: [Srmlandstrafiken](https://sormlandstrafiken.se/)\r\n\r\nRemember that members of SveKub travel with up to 10% discount with SJ, more information is available on Sverok\'s [website](https://medlem.sverok.se/reserabatt/). Trips with all of Sweden\'s public transport companies can be searched via [Resrobot.se](https://resrobot.se/).',5,'Resa / Travel'),
(43627,'24HoursinAker2024','## Liveresultat\r\nUnder tvlingen kan ni se liveresultat p [WCA Live](https://live.worldcubeassociation.org).\r\nDet r ocks dr du kan se dina egna tider och om du gick vidare till nsta omgng eller inte. \r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Live Results\r\nDuring the competition you can see live results on [WCA Live](https://live.worldcubeassociation.org).\r\nThat is also where you can see your own times and whether you advanced to the next round or not.',7,'Liveresultat / Live Results'),
(43628,'24HoursinAker2024','[![](https://cuboss.se/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/logo_400.png)](https://cuboss.se/?r=wca)\r\n\r\n### Sponsorer & Priser\r\nTvlingen sponsras av kub-butiken [Cuboss.se](https://cuboss.se/?r=wca)! Cuboss r en svensk onlinebutik specialiserad p speedcubes och andra typer av pussel, vilka de levererar bde inom Sverige samt till resten av vrlden. Cuboss har valt att sponsra tvlingen med presentkort till enligt nedan.\r\n\r\nPallplatsen i 3x3x3 tilldelas presentkort frn Cuboss enligt fljande:\r\n1:a plats: 150 kr\r\n2:a plats: 100 kr\r\n3:e plats: 50 kr\r\n\r\nPallplatsen i tvlingens \"sum of ranks\", allts bst placeringar i alla grenar verlag, tilldelas presentkort frn Cuboss enligt fljande:\r\n1:a plats: 150 kr\r\n2:a plats: 100 kr\r\n3:e plats: 50 kr\r\n\r\nDessutom kommer tv presentkort p Cuboss vrda 50 kr att lottas ut till deltagare p prisceremonin, dr alla som nrvarar har chans att vinna ett!\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n### Sponsors & Prizes\r\nThe competition is sponsored by the cube store [Cuboss.com](https://cuboss.com/?r=wca)! Cuboss is an online cube store based in Sweden, specializing in speedcubes and other types of puzzles, with worldwide delivery available. Cuboss has generously chosen to sponsor the competition with gift cards for the medalists in the various event as outlined below:\r\n\r\nThe podium of 3x3x3 will receive the following gift cards from Cuboss:\r\n1st place: 150 SEK\r\n2nd place: 100 SEK\r\n3rd place: 50 SEK\r\n\r\nThe podium of the competition\'s \"sum of ranks\", the people who get the best placements over all events, will receive the following gift cards from Cuboss:\r\n1st place: 150 SEK\r\n2nd place: 100 SEK\r\n3rd place: 50 SEK\r\n\r\nIn addition, two gift cards worth 50 SEK will be randomly drawn to competitors at the award ceremony, where everyone who attends has a chance to win one!',8,'Sponsorer & Priser / Sponsors & Prizes'),
(43667,'24HoursinAker2024','### Svenska\r\n#### Koncept\r\nDenna tvling kommer pg frn lrdag 14:00 till sndag 15:00, med omgngar under hela natten.\r\nOmgngarna och deras tidstgng r frutbestmda, men ordningen kommer avgras av slumpen under tvlingen. Efter varje omgng snurras ett hjul som avgr vad nsta omgng blir. Detta pgr under hela tvlingen tills omgngarna r slut och 24 timmar har uppntts. Sjlvklart kommer eventuella finalrundor dock inte kunna hllas innan den frsta rundan i samma gren r genomfrd.\r\n\r\n**Obs:** Vnligen notera att detta r en mycket speciell tvling med helt andra frutsttningar r vanligt. Det kommer innebra en stor pfrestning, och vi rekommenderar att tnka efter om du kommer ha mjlighet att genomfra tvlingen. Tvlingen rekommenderas varken fr yngre barn eller fr helt nya deltagare.\r\n\r\n#### 24 timmar 3BLD (+ eventuella andra inofficiella sidogrenar)\r\nUtver de vanliga omgngarna kommer en specialgren ordnas, en 3BLD-lsning som strcker sig ver 24 timmar. Alla som vill delta fr vid incheckningen memorera en 3x3, sedan dljs kuben tills slutet av tvlingen, d man lser den med gonbindel. Tiden mts fr bde memoreringen p lrdagen och exekveringen p sndagen. Mellan memorering och lsning fr inga fysiska noteringar gras, precis som under vanlig blindlsning. Det r allts exempelvis inte tilltet att skriva ner sin memorering, eller gra den baklnges p en annan kub fr att kunna \"va\" p sin lsning.\r\n\r\nDet kan hnda att det blir andra inofficiella sidogrenar ocks, lite beroende p hur vi ligger till i schemat samt hur mnga officiella rundor vi har kvar nr dygnet brjar n sitt slut. Eventuella sdana inofficiella grenar annonseras p plats i lokalen.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n### English\r\n#### Concept\r\nThis competition will run from Saturday 2 pm to Sunday 3 pm, with rounds throughout the night.\r\nThe rounds and their durations are predetermined, but the order will be determined by chance during the competition. After each round, a wheel is spun which determines what the next round will be. This goes on throughout the competition until the rounds are over and 24 hours have passed. Of course, any final rounds will not be held before the first round in the same event has been completed.\r\n\r\n**Note:** Please note that this is a very special competition with completely different conditions than usual. It will be very tiring, and we recommend thinking about whether you will actually be able to complete the competition. The competition is not recommended for younger children or for completely new participants.\r\n\r\n#### 24 hours 3BLD (+ potential other unofficial side events)\r\nIn addition to the regular rounds, a special event will be organized, a 3BLD solve that spans 24 hours. Everyone who wishes to take part memorizes a 3x3 at check-in, then the cube is hidden until the end of the competition, when it is solved blindfolded. The time is measured for both the memorization on Saturday and the execution on Sunday. Between memorizing and solving it is not permitted to make physical notes, just like in normal blindfolded solving. This means you are not allowed to for example write down your memo, or execute it backwards on another cube to \"practice\" your solution.\r\n\r\nIt may happen that there will be other unofficial side events as well, depending on how well we adhere to the schedule and how many official rounds we have left when the competition starts to come to an end. Any such unofficial events will be announced on site.',1,'Koncept / Concept'),
(43668,'24HoursinAker2024','### Mat\r\n\r\nI schemat ligger tre matpauser inlagda. En middagspaus p lrdag kvll, en paus mitt i natten, och en fr frukost p sndag morgon. Det finns en pizzeria och en ICA-butik i nrheten av lokalen. Bde pizzerian och ICA stnger kl 21:00, s tnk p att kpa det du behver i tid s du orkar med natten. I lokalen finns tillgng till kylskp och mikrovgsugn.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n### Food\r\n\r\nThere are three food breaks in the schedule. One dinner break on Saturday night, one break in the middle of the night, and a breakfast break on Sunday morning. There is a pizzeria and an ICA grocery store near the venue. They both close at 9:00 PM, so remember to buy everything you need in time to manage the night. There is a fridge and a microwave available in the venue.\r\n\r\n',6,'Mat / Food'),
(45283,'200Peru2024','Este es el torneo nmero 200 en Per!\r\n\r\n**LIMITE**\r\nEl torneo tiene un lmite en el nmero de participantes igual a 100. Recomendamos completar el registro con la debida anticipacin.\r\nEl registro se cerrar cuando el lmite de participantes se alcance, o en su defecto el jueves 11 de julio.\r\n\r\n**COSTO**\r\nEl costo de la inscripcin es de 8 soles de base (incluye una modalidad) y 2 soles por modalidad adicional. Ver detalles de pago ms abajo.\r\n\r\n**REGISTRO**\r\nSe recomienda seguir los siguientes pasos para completar exitsamente el registro:\r\n1. Conocer el [reglamento de la WCA](https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/regulations/) ya que este es un torneo oficial.\r\n2. Elegir los eventos a inscribir cuidadosamente luego de revisar la pestaa Horario. Prestar atencin a los formato de las rondas y a sus cortes y lmites.\r\n3. Inscribirse electrnicamente completando el proceso [aqu](https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/competitions/200Peru2024/register). Quienes participan por primera vez deberan crear una cuenta en la WCA para lo cual requieren tener un correo vlido.\r\n4. Hacer el pago de la inscripcin en el local de la [tienda The Cube Girls](http://thecubegirls.com/tiendas/) en Arequipa, o coordinando otras formas de pago con [Natn Riggenbach](https://www.facebook.com/natanrig) (Facebook o WhatsApp: 958461002).\r\n5. Esperar a que el registro electrnico sea aceptado.\r\n\r\n\r\n**RESULTADOS PRELIMINARES**\r\nLos resultados preliminares, y los clasificados a rondas posteriores, se podrn ver casi en tiempo real en [WCALive](https://live.worldcubeassociation.org).\r\n\r\n',1,'Informacin Adicional'),
(47147,'2x2at2inPrague2024','DDM Ulita se nachz cca pt minut chze od tramvajov zastvky Strn (linka 11, 29, 31, 98).\r\nParkovn je mon v okolnch ulicch. Od ptench 17:00 je zdarma.\r\n\r\nDDM Ulita is located approx. 5 minutes away from the tram stop \"Strn\" (tram no. 11, 29, 31, 98).\r\nParking spots are available in surrounding streets. It is free starting Friday, 17:00.',1,'Cestovn/Travel'),
(47148,'2x2at2inPrague2024','**CZ:**\r\nNa tto souti budou neoficiln eventy, konkrtn 2x2x2-4x4x4 Relay. Vsledky budou zaznamenny pes [Cubing Contests](https://cubingcontests.com) a pot pidny do celosvtovch ebk.\r\n\r\nPokud chcete soutit, napite to prosm do poznmky k registraci.\r\n\r\n[Vsledky](https://cubingcontests.com/competitions/2x2at2inPrague2024)\r\n\r\n[Podrobnosti k eventm](https://cubingcontests.com/competitions/2x2at2inPrague2024/events)\r\n\r\n**EN:**\r\nThis competition will also hold unofficial events, more specifically 2x2x2-4x4x4 Relay. The results will be recorded through [Cubing Contests](https://cubingcontests.com), and will then be added to the rankings.\r\n\r\nIf you want to compete, please leave a note about it in your registration.\r\n\r\n[Live Results](https://cubingcontests.com/competitions/2x2at2inPrague2024)\r\n\r\n[Event Details](https://cubingcontests.com/competitions/2x2at2inPrague2024/events)\r\n',3,'Neoficiln Eventy/Unofficial Events'),
(47163,'2x2at2inPrague2024','V okol se nachzej restaurace, rychl oberstven a veerky. Piblin 1 km od venue najdete tak supermarket, kter m oteveno do 22:00.\r\n\r\nThere are restaurants, fast food restaurants and corner shops nearby. Approx. 1 km away from the venue is a supermarket, open untill 22:00.',2,'Jdlo/Food'),
(47610,'10thAnniversaryCervantes2024','# ![](https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/redirect/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBaGxIIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--e1a87d9563999f890af638f98836b63b2aac90c5/6u.png) Espaol \r\n\r\n**Es de extrema importancia la puntualidad. Tenga en cuenta que el competidor puede ser descalificado de una categora por llegar tarde, segn la [Regla 2u](https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/regulations/#2u) (esto es necesario ya que en caso contrario el torneo podra retrasarse). Se sugiere presentarse al menos 15 minutos antes de cada ronda.**\r\n\r\nSe recomienda que las personas que tengan el registro pendiente se mantengan atentas por si se libera algn lugar o alguien no se presenta el da de la competencia.\r\n\r\nEs obligacin de los competidores estar familiarizados con el [Reglamento de la WCA](https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/regulations/translations/spanish-american/).\r\nLos competidores pueden ser requeridos para desempear ciertas tareas, segn se describe en las reglas [1e2](https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/regulations/translations/spanish-american/#1e2) y [1f2](https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/regulations/translations/spanish-american/#1f2), de lo contrario, la competencia podra retrasarse.\r\n\r\nEl competidor es la nica persona responsable de que los resultados en la hoja de resultados:\r\n* Sean correctos.\r\n* Sean legibles (si un nmero no se entiende bien, debe pedirle al juez que lo arregle antes de firmar el intento).\r\n* Est firmado tanto por el juez como por el competidor. Penalizacin por firmas que faltan: descalificacin del intento afectado (DNF).\r\n\r\n***\r\n\r\n# ![](https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/redirect/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBaHBIIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--bacb00caed7d0c9177dc3ea7d687667b270ce30d/6i.png) English \r\n\r\n**It is extremely important to be punctual for each round. Bear in mind that competitors may be disqualified under the circumstances described in [Regulation 2u](https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/regulations/#2u). It is recommended to arrive at least 15 minutes before the start of each round. This is necessary to avoid delays in the schedule.**\r\n\r\nWe recommend people with a pending registration to remain alert in case a spot becomes available or someone does not show up the day of the competition.\r\n\r\nCompetitors must be familiarized with the [WCA Regulations](https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/regulations/).\r\nCompetitors may be required to help with specific tasks, as described in regulations [1e2](https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/regulations/translations/#1e2) and [1f2](https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/regulations/#1f2).\r\n\r\nThe competitor must make sure that the results on the scoresheet are:\r\n* Correct, complete, properly formatted, and clearly readable.\r\n* Signed by the Judge and the Competitor. Penalty for missing signatures: Did Not Finish (DNF).',1,'Importante / Read'),
(47611,'10thAnniversaryCervantes2024','# \r\n\r\nEn caso de ser la primera competencia a la que asiste, deber presentar el documento de identidad (o pasaporte), como consta en la [Regla 2e](https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/regulations/#2e) del Reglamento y las Directrices de la WCA.\r\nAdems debe leer el [Reglamento de la WCA](https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/regulations/) antes de la competencia, segn el [Regla 2t](https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/regulations/#2t) del Reglamento de la WCA.\r\n\r\nHay disponible una [versin en espaol del Reglamento de la WCA](https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/regulations/translations/spanish-american/), pero se debe tener en cuenta que ante diferencias entre dicha versin y la oficial (en ingls), la versin oficial prevalecer.\r\n\r\nLos resultados de los competidores se publican en tiempo real en [WCA Live](https://live.worldcubeassociation.org/). Por cualquier duda, consultar a los organizadores.\r\n\r\nVideo con procedimientos y reglas bsicas para competir:\r\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PFCBh3i7TiY\r\n\r\nManual para competidores (en espaol):\r\nhttps://www.worldcubeassociation.org/edudoc/competitor-tutorial/tutorial_es.pdf\r\n\r\nManual para jueces (en espaol, tambin deben tenerlo en cuenta los competidores):\r\nhttps://www.worldcubeassociation.org/edudoc/judge-tutorial/judge-tutorial-es.pdf\r\n \r\n ***\r\n\r\n# \r\n\r\nIf this is your first competition ever, you must provide an ID document (i.e. a passport), as stated in [Regulation 2e] (https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/regulations/#2e) of the WCA Regulations and Guidelines.\r\nYou must also read the [WCA Regulations](https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/regulations/) before the competition, as per [Regulation 2t](https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/regulations/#2t) of the WCA Regulations.\r\n\r\nCompetitor\'s results will be available in [WCA Live](https://live.worldcubeassociation.org/). You can always reach out to the Organizers and/or the WCA Delegates if you have any question.\r\n\r\nVideo with basic rules and procedures for official attempts:\r\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dPL3eV-A0ww\r\n\r\nCompetitor tutorial:\r\nhttps://www.worldcubeassociation.org/edudoc/competitor-tutorial/tutorial.pdf\r\n\r\nJudging tutorial:\r\nhttps://www.worldcubeassociation.org/edudoc/judge-tutorial/judge-tutorial.pdf',2,'Competidores nuevos / Newcomers'),
(47612,'10thAnniversaryCervantes2024','# \r\nSegn la regla [2s](https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/regulations/translations/spanish-american/#2s), los competidores con diversidad funcional que se vean impedidos de cumplir con una o ms reglas de la WCA, pueden solicitar adaptaciones especiales al delegado de la WCA. Los competidores que requieran estas adaptaciones deben ponerse en contacto con el equipo organizador y el delegado de la WCA al menos dos semanas antes de la competicin.\r\n\r\n***\r\n# \r\nAs per regulation [2s](https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/regulations/#2s): \"Competitors with disabilities that may prevent them from abiding by one or more WCA regulations may request special accommodations from the WCA Delegate. Competitors requesting such accommodations should contact the organization team and WCA Delegate at least two weeks before the competition\".',3,'Necesidades especiales / Special accommodations'),
