('1stDibrugarhOpen2018',0,0,'2018-10-12 12:22:29',341,NULL,0,NULL,30000,NULL,NULL,'1st Dibrugarh Open 2018','Dibrugarh, Assam',NULL,0,50,0,'Organizing team is very new and they have entry constraints as well.','2018-10-12 06:32:46',NULL,'Kabyanil  - 7086733737    Nekibur - 8723043562 ','India','2018-10-11 18:11:22','INR',0,'',0,'2018-11-10',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Step 1 - Register on WCA by selecting the events you want to participate in.\r\nStep 2 - Pay the registration fee at the entrance of the college where a registration kiosk will be set up by Auxesis team.\r\n\r\nPayment fee structure:\r\n\r\nBase fee (One event) - 300 INR\r\nFor every extra event - 50 INR\r\n\r\n**EXAMPLE**\r\nSo if you are participating in 3 events, you need to pay 300(Base fee) + 100(for remaining 2 events) = 400 INR\r\n',0,NULL,NULL,1,0,1,0,NULL,'The competition is open to all competitors. No experience in WCA competitions is necessary, but competitors should be familiar with the regulations and certain event-based time limits will be in place. \r\n\r\n**Steps to register on spot:**\r\nSpot registration will be open from 8:00 a.m to 11:00 am on the day of competition for events that haven\'t started by the time you register.\r\nPlease bring your ID cards for identification at the college gate.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nPlease check information regarding payment and schedule under the respective tabs.',27451715,94890372,'333','1st Dibrugarh Open 2018','',NULL,30000,1,NULL,0,'',NULL,0,'2018-11-09 18:29:00','2018-10-10 00:00:00',NULL,'remarks to the board here',NULL,'2018-11-15 17:18:21',9,'2018-11-15 17:18:21',1,'2018-11-10','2018-11-15 17:18:21',0,1,'[Dibrugarh University, Dibrugarh](https://www.dibru.ac.in/)','Dibrugarh University, NH-37, Rajapeta, Dibrugarh, Assam 786004','Core Building, DUIET',NULL),
('1stJorhatOpen2019',0,0,'2019-08-05 08:33:15',249,NULL,0,NULL,25000,NULL,NULL,'1st Jorhat Open 2019','Jorhat, Assam',NULL,0,100,1,'Organizing team is very new and they have entry constraints as well.','2019-08-02 05:56:08',NULL,'','India','2019-08-01 11:41:09','INR',0,'',0,'2019-09-15',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'**Steps to register online:**\r\n*First time participants*\r\nStep 1 - Sign-up on WCA\r\nStep 2 - Register for the competition\r\n\r\n*Other participants*\r\nStep 1 - Sign-in using your email that you used for your previous competitions\r\nStep 2 - Register for the competition (ensure your WCA id is mentioned)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n**Steps to register on spot:**\r\nSpot registration will be open from 8:00 a.m to 9:00 am on the day 1 (14-September-2019) of competition for all the events.\r\nPlease bring your ID cards for identification at the college gate.\r\n\r\n\r\n**Payment fee structure:**\r\n\r\n(Onspot)\r\nBase fee (One event) - 250 INR\r\nFor every extra event - 50 INR\r\n\r\n\r\n**EXAMPLE**\r\nSo if you are participating in 3 events, you need to pay 250(Base fee) + 100(for remaining 2 events) = 350 INR\r\n',0,NULL,NULL,1,0,1,0,NULL,'The competition is open to all competitors. No experience in WCA competitions is necessary, however competitors should be familiar with the regulations.\r\n',26745562,94249915,'333','1st Jorhat Open 2019','Jorhat is the city name and the competition is happening for the first time..',NULL,25000,1,NULL,0,'',NULL,0,'2019-09-12 00:00:00','2019-08-09 00:00:00',NULL,'remarks to the board here',NULL,'2019-09-16 18:05:07',2,'2019-09-16 11:25:31',1,'2019-09-14','2019-09-16 18:05:07',0,1,'Jorhat Engineering College','Jorhat Engineering College , Garmur , Jorhat , Assam - 785007','Auditorium ',NULL),
('1stSalemOpen2022',1,0,'2022-05-25 13:40:38',1583,NULL,0,NULL,50000,NULL,NULL,'1st Salem Open 2022','Salem, Tamil Nadu',NULL,0,100,1,'This is the maximum count the venue can hold.','2022-05-23 07:17:11',NULL,'','India','2022-05-19 12:35:27','INR',0,'',0,'2022-06-26','2022-06-26 00:00:00',0,'',NULL,'',NULL,'**Steps to complete Online registration**\r\nStep 1 - Register [here](https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/competitions/1stSalemOpen2022/register) by selecting the events you want to participate in.\r\nStep 2 - Make the payment of INR 500 using any of the following payment methods.\r\nStep 3 - Wait up to 48 hours for your registration to be confirmed. Once your registration is confirmed, you will get a confirmation mail and your name will appear in the list of [registered competitors](https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/competitions/1stSalemOpen2022/registrations).\r\n\r\n[//]: # (**Steps to complete On the spot registration**)\r\n[//]: # (Step 1 - Arrive at the venue by 8:15AM on Competition Day. )\r\n[//]: # (Step 2 - Remaining slots from Online registrations will be filled through On the spot registrations using First come first serve basis. )\r\n[//]: # (Step 3 - Make the payment of INR 800 using UPI method or by Cash. (Debit/Credit cards will not be accepted)\r\n\r\n[//]: # (Payment Methods:)\r\n[//]: # (PhonePe -  Pay registration fee to 7401787282@ybl using PhonePe app. Add the details of the participant as a comment during the payment.)\r\n[//]: # (Google Pay - Pay registration fees to mohamedarif5412@okicici using Google Pay app. Add the details of the participant as a comment during the payment.)\r\n[//]: # (On the spot registration - Cash or UPI method.)\r\n',0,NULL,NULL,1,0,0,0,NULL,'* Kindly bring your ID card while entering the campus.\r\n* Wearing masks all the time and sanitizing hands frequently is mandatory for both Participants and guests. \r\n* If you\'re participating in a WCA competition for first time or unaware of competition rules, make sure that you attend the tutorial session.\r\n* Participants must bring their own cubes.\r\n* Slots left over from Online registrations will be filled through On the spot registrations. The slots will be filled according to First come First serve basis. \r\n* For example: If 75 slots are filled through Online registrations, only 25 slots will be opened for On the spot registrations. So, we recommend the competitors to reserve their place in the competition through online payments. \r\n* If all the 100 slots are filled through Online registrations, then there will not be any On the spot registrations.\r\n* Kindly make your own arrangements for your food. \r\n',11692463,78064693,'333','1st Salem Open 2022','This will be the first ever competition in the city of Salem, Tamil Nadu',NULL,80000,0,NULL,0,'',NULL,0,'2022-06-09 10:40:00','2022-05-30 00:00:00','2022-05-29 00:00:19','remarks to the board here',NULL,'2022-06-28 19:05:49',1197,'2022-06-28 14:40:37',1,'2022-06-26','2022-06-28 19:05:49',1,1,'Mukundha International School','DPC Campus, Chettiarkadai Bus Stop, Muthunaicken Patty, Pagalpatty [PO], Salem, Tamil Nadu, 636304','Activity Room, Mukundha International School','2022-06-22 00:00:00'),
('1stSriLankanOpen2022',1,0,'2022-02-18 19:02:19',17812,NULL,0,NULL,250000,NULL,NULL,'1st Sri Lankan Open 2022','Colombo',NULL,0,35,1,'Organizers are new and they are inexperienced. We wanted to host a small competition to kick start the culture of WCA competitions in the country \"Sri Lanka\"','2022-02-18 12:46:55',NULL,'','Sri Lanka','2022-02-13 08:33:19','LKR',0,'',0,'2022-04-02','2022-03-27 00:00:00',0,'',NULL,'',NULL,'Steps to complete online registration\r\nStep 1 - Register [here](https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/competitions/1stSriLankanOpen2022/register) by selecting the events you want to participate in.\r\nStep 2 - Make the payment through one of the below mentioned methods.\r\nStep 3 - Wait upto 48 hours for your registration to be confirmed. Once your registration is confirmed, you will get a confirmation mail and your name will appear in the list of registered competitors.\r\n\r\nPlease note that your registration will be processed manually only after the payment of required fees.\r\n\r\n\r\nPayment details : \r\n\r\n\r\nFor **local payments** (Srilankan), deposit or Online transfer LKR 2,500.00 using one of following options:\r\n\r\n* Bank transfer to:\r\n116856045161\r\nW.M.K.S. Wijesundara,\r\nSampath Bank,\r\nAnuradhapura New Town\r\n\r\nMake sure to add a comment with the participant name while transferring the money. If possible, kindly send a screenshot of the payment to the organizer through email ([kalindu.sachintha@gmail.com](mailto:kalindu.sachintha@gmail.com)). \r\n\r\n* Send via FriMi Mobile wallet transfer application to: FriMi ID 2222147359\r\n\r\nMake sure to add a comment with the participant name while transferring the money. If possible, kindly send a screenshot of the payment to the organizer through email ([kalindu.sachintha@gmail.com](mailto:kalindu.sachintha@gmail.com)). \r\n\r\n\r\nFor **international payments**, pay USD 13.00 through paypal account - https://www.paypal.me/sivasachin26gmailcom\r\n\r\nMake sure to add a comment with the participant name while transferring the money. If possible, kindly send a screenshot of the payment to the organizer through email ([kalindu.sachintha@gmail.com](mailto:kalindu.sachintha@gmail.com)). \r\n\r\n',0,NULL,NULL,1,2,1,0,NULL,'* Make sure you will be available at the venue at least 15 minutes before your event starts. You won\'t be allowed to participate in an event if you reach late. You can refer \"Schedule\" tab to see the starting time of each event.\r\n* If you\'re participating in a WCA competition for the first time or not aware of competition rules, make sure that you attend the tutorial session at 9:00 a.m.\r\n* If you\'re participating in a WCA competition for the first time, please bring your ID card as well. (NIC/Passport/Postal ID/Driving License)\r\n* All participants are expected to volunteer for the event when they are not participating. The roles could be of a judge, runner, or a scrambler, depending upon the situation.\r\n\r\nCOVID-19 Specific Information:\r\n\r\n* Wearing masks, frequently sanitizing hands and following all local goverment health guidelines is mandatory while attending the competition.\r\n* All the participants, guests/spectators should be fully vaccinated (at least two doses). Please bring proof of vaccination with you.\r\n* If you are not vaccinated, you must provide proof of a negative COVID-19 Rapid Antigen test within 72 hours before the start of competition. In case of failing to submit the proof, Organizing team can deny entry to such participants to the competition. And No refund will be allowed in that case.\r\n* We strongly recommend limiting the number of guests you bring for the safety of all attendees. The maximum number of guests that is preferred to accompay a competitor would be limited to TWO.\r\n',6879843,79934466,'333','1st Sri Lankan Open 2022','This is the first ever WCA competition in this country',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,'','2022-03-27 00:00:00',0,'2022-03-22 19:45:00','2022-02-22 12:30:00','