idates with the leader following application submission. The week after the application period, the committee/team will make a selection and the new members will be announced once candidates have accepted the positions.\r\n\r\nThank you for your candidacies and support!','2018-01-13 22:52:17',1,'committee-team-membership-application-deadlines-extended',0,'Committee/Team Membership Application Deadlines Extended!',NULL,'2018-01-22 05:02:44'),
(8744,277,'TNoodle-WCA-0.13.1 is now available from https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/regulations/scrambles/\r\nThe following changes have been made since TNoodle 0.12.0:\r\n\r\n - TNoodle now supports connecting to the WCA website to retrieve the events and rounds of a competition.\r\n - FMC sheets are now available in 22 languages. The full list is available here: https://github.com/thewca/tnoodle/tree/v0.13.1/webscrambles/src/i18n.\r\n	\r\nPlease remember that official competitions must use the current version of the official scramble program. This is always available from:\r\nhttps://www.worldcubeassociation.org/regulations/scrambles/','2018-01-29 17:04:08',1,'tnoodle-0-13-1',0,'TNoodle 0.13.1',NULL,'2018-02-03 16:23:34'),
(8781,277,'TNoodle-WCA-0.13.2 is now available from https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/regulations/scrambles/\r\nThe following changes have been made since TNoodle 0.12.0:\r\n\r\n - TNoodle now supports connecting to the WCA website to retrieve the events and rounds of a competition.\r\n - FMC sheets are now available in 22 languages. The full list is available here: https://github.com/thewca/tnoodle/tree/v0.13.2/webscrambles/src/i18n.\r\n\r\nThis new release fixes a bug occurring in specific browsers with TNoodle 0.13.1, where the generated zip file would miss its extension.\r\nBoth TNoodle 0.13.2 and TNoodle 0.13.1 are current versions of the scramble program, and either can be used to generate scrambles for a competition.\r\n\r\nPlease remember that official competitions must use a current version of the official scramble program. This is always available from:\r\nhttps://www.worldcubeassociation.org/regulations/scrambles/','2018-02-03 16:23:28',1,'tnoodle-0-13-2',0,'TNoodle 0.13.2',NULL,'2018-02-05 21:00:42'),
(8801,277,'TNoodle-WCA-0.13.3 is now available from https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/regulations/scrambles/\r\nThe following changes have been made since TNoodle 0.12.0:\r\n\r\n - TNoodle now supports connecting to the WCA website to retrieve the events and rounds of a competition.\r\n - FMC sheets are now available in 22 languages. The full list is available here: https://github.com/thewca/tnoodle/tree/v0.13.2/webscrambles/src/i18n.\r\n\r\nThis new release fixes a serious bug occurring in specific browsers with TNoodle 0.13.1, where the generated zip file would miss its extension.\r\nIt fixes another serious bug in TNoodle 0.13.2 and TNoodle 0.13.1 where the rounds ids were wrongly generated in the scrambles json file, making it impossible to use in the Workbook Assistant.\r\n\r\nAppologies for any inconvenience these multiple TNoodle releases may have caused.\r\n\r\nPlease remember that official competitions must use a current version of the official scramble program. This is always available from:\r\nhttps://www.worldcubeassociation.org/regulations/scrambles/','2018-02-05 21:00:38',1,'tnoodle-0-13-3',0,'TNoodle 0.13.3',NULL,'2018-02-24 19:21:11'),
(8950,1338,'Dear WCA Community,\r\n\r\nThe WCA is taking large steps towards registering as a 501(c)(3) non-profit soon and part of this process requires the WCA to have a consistent revenue stream to afford monthly and annual expenses.\r\n\r\nThis year we will be introducing the WCA Dues System. This is a fee per competition, based on the number of competitors and cost of living for that country, that will be owed to the WCA. The fee is small and is intended to be integrated into the registration payments you would see at most competitions. This is so that competitors will not see a big change in registration fees once the system is introduced. The delegate(s) for the competition will be responsible for paying this fee, however organizers should be aware that this fee must be paid and should work with the delegates to make sure this cost is covered.  We started a pilot in the USA and the UK in January 2018 and we will implement the system worldwide for competitions announced from March 1, 2018 onward. This will not affect registration fees for already announced competitions. \r\n\r\nWith the revenue, the WCA will be able to cover the base costs of running the WCA organization, like our website, mailbox, legal representation, and the formal reporting obligations of the WCA. This will ensure continuity of the WCA. In addition to the operational costs, we also want to invest in strategic developments, like further professionalization, worldwide availability of equipment, and spreading of our competitions to new countries and areas. \r\nOnce we are a full non-profit we will also seek cooperation with sponsors to further develop our sport, the WCA organization, and our community.\r\n\r\nYou can find the [official documentation about the dues system](https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/documents/policies/Dues%20System.pdf) on our website. For specific questions you may have, please reach out to the WCA using [finance@worldcubeassociation.org](mailto:finance@worldcubeassociation.org) and we would be happy to answer them! Thank you for your cooperation as we begin this exciting process!','2018-03-01 05:19:19',0,'introduction-of-wca-dues-system',0,'Introduction of WCA Dues System',NULL,'2020-12-08 10:25:05'),
(8957,1338,'We are happy to announce that South American Championship will be held in the city of Po-So Paulo, Brazil on December 15-16!\r\n\r\nApplications were received from Po-SP and for an idea to hold the championship across multiple cities in South America. Both described the details for hosting the competition in their own unique ways and had a lot of thought put into them. In the end, Po-So Paulo was chosen as the host city.\r\n\r\nBoth applications can be found [here](https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/19jgWuE4_fOU1MMAePp2clrOucyKl0ylf?usp=sharing).\r\n\r\nThank you to those who put together both applications for their time and effort in planning for this competition! It is exciting to see enthusiasm for our larger competitions from those who take the time to apply to host them and their planning is appreciated.\r\n\r\nWe look forward to another South American Championship in December and hope you can join us!','2018-03-02 05:25:14',1,'information-about-south-american-championship',0,'Information about South American Championship',NULL,'2018-05-08 16:54:26'),
(9097,4,'The [WCA Asian Championship 2018](https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/competitions/AsianChampionship2018) will take place on August 17 - 19, 2018 in Taipei, Taiwan. Check out the [WCA Asian Championship 2018 website](https://cubing-tw.net/event/2018AsianChampionship/) for more information and registration.','2018-03-22 00:26:18',1,'wca-asian-championship-2018-on-august-17-19-2018-in-taipei-taiwan',0,'WCA Asian Championship 2018 on August 17 - 19, 2018 in Taipei, Taiwan',NULL,'2018-08-19 09:33:48'),
(9376,2,'[Martin Fronescu](https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/persons/2013FRON01) won the [U.R.A. Spring of Colors 2018](https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/competitions/URASpringofColors2018) with an average of 8.68 seconds. [Sorin Turcule](https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/persons/2017TURC02) finished second (10.53) and [Jnos Bereczki](https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/persons/2018BERE01) finished third (10.78).\n\n','2018-04-30 14:57:07',1,'martin-fronescu-wins-u-r-a-spring-of-colors-2018-in-bucharest-romania',0,'Martin Fronescu wins U.R.A. Spring of Colors 2018, in Bucharest, Romania',NULL,'2018-05-08 11:16:08'),
(9381,1338,'There will be an appointment of a new WCA Committee Leader. Chris Hardwick is stepping down as the Leader of the **WCA Financial Committee**, and thus as the **WCA Treasurer**.\r\n\r\nChris has done a great work as the Leader of the WFC and as the Treasurer of the WCA, and we thank him for all his hard work and dedication all this time, as well as wish him the best in all his future endeavors.\r\n\r\nCandidates are expected to fulfill their terms (24 months) and to spend at least 6 hours per week on average to work for the Committee. \r\nThe qualities expected of candidates are:\r\n- Basic knowledge of the structure and workflow inside the WCA.\r\n- Experience on financial matters, especially bookkeeping and tax filing.\r\n- Proficiency in English.\r\n- A reasonable daily availability to deploy the duties.\r\n- Team management capabilities.\r\n\r\nThe application period is opened for candidates to submit their candidacy documents until **May 8th, 2018, 23:59 UTC** privately to the WCA Board ([board@worldcubeassociation.org](mailto:board@worldcubeassociation.org))\r\n<!-- break -->\r\n**The candidacy documents must be in PDF format, and must include:**\r\n- Brief personal introduction.\r\n- Summary of activities done for the WCA.\r\n- Ambitions as the WFC Leader and the Treasurer of the WCA.\r\n\r\nThe rights and duties of the WFC are copied from [WCA Motion 10.2017.3](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1mTeKEXe0DzD8olEQF_sy37OKtFcAPhAc/edit) in an appendix below.\r\n\r\nThe week after the application period, the WCA Board will make a selection by voting and will announce the new Leader, after confirmation among Senior Delegates and sitting Committee/Team Leaders by voting, as described in Section 4 of [WCA Motion 10.2017.0](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1NDLzup8rbfw8En0S6vtChNti9IKopDBq/edit).\r\n\r\nThank you for your candidacies and support.\r\n\r\n*APPENDIX - RIGHTS AND DUTIES OF WCA FINANCIAL COMMITTEE*\r\n\r\n1. The WCA Financial Committee is an Advisory Committee of the WCA with the following rights and duties:\r\n        1. Creating an annual budget proposal for the WCA.\r\n        2. Managing the finances and accounts of the WCA in accordance with the approved annual budget proposal.\r\n        3. Paying invoices and taxes that are directed to the WCA, after procuration by the WCA Board of Directors.\r\n        4. Reporting and advising on a quarterly basis to the WCA Board of Directors on the finances of the WCA.\r\n        5. Reporting on a periodic basis to external organizations on the finances of the WCA, based on all applicable legal requirements.\r\n        6. Appointing and supporting financial auditors based on all applicable legal requirements.\r\n2. The Leader of the WCA Financial Committee is the Treasurer of the WCA.\r\n','2018-05-01 04:06:59',1,'appointment-of-a-new-wca-financial-committee-leader-may-2018',0,'Appointment of a New WCA Financial Committee Leader (May 2018)',NULL,'2019-07-02 12:10:03'),
(9436,1338,'The WCA Board of Directors are accepting applications for WCA World Championship 2019.\r\n\r\nPlease discuss with the Delegates in your country whether this is something you are willing and able to pursue. Bear in mind that organizing a competition of this size takes a significant amount of time and effort before and during the competition.\r\n\r\nIf you are interested, send your application documents privately to [albertopdrf.wca@gmail.com](mailto:albertopdrf.wca@gmail.com) **before 23:59 UTC of July 15th, 2018**. **Documents must be sent in PDF format in two versions:** one full version with all the details for the application, and another version with sensitive details - if any - removed to make public.\r\n<!-- break -->\r\nPlease include in your application documents at least the following information:\r\n\r\nWhen would you like to hold WC 2019?\r\n1a. Possible dates\r\n1b. Number of days of the competition.\r\n1c. Overlap with international holiday periods of schools.\r\n\r\nWhere would you like to hold WC 2019 in your country?\r\n2a. City should be interesting to visit for foreigners with opportunities for sightseeing.\r\n2b. Ease of international, national, and local travel.\r\n2c. Availability of hotels/apartments with different price categories.\r\n2d. Venue, venue size, and venue setup (stage, audience, tables to practice, side rooms).\r\n2e. Technology available like internet, video streaming, lighting, sound equipment.\r\n2f. Number of competitors and spectators that can be hosted.\r\n\r\nWhat would the organization team and staff look like?\r\n3a. Core team members.\r\n3b. Experience of the core team.\r\n3c. Involvement of other parties.\r\n3d. Quantity and quality of local volunteers (guideline is 20% of competitors should staff).\r\n3e. Required support by foreign Delegates.\r\n\r\nWhat would be the overall budget for the competition?\r\n4a. Cost (venue, venue services, stage, equipment, decorations, website, badges/lanyards/giftpacks, prizes).\r\n4b. Income (registration fees, sponsoring, local government).\r\n\r\nHere is an example document with a non-exhaustive list of topics that need to be arranged and budgeted for a large competition: [https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1w6uxOHrr40of1R4-NjU1vy7fVJXRHiRZBn53Hc-IOk8](https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1w6uxOHrr40of1R4-NjU1vy7fVJXRHiRZBn53Hc-IOk8)\r\n\r\nOnce the application period is over, the WCA Board of Directors will interview applicants, consult other WCA Staff members, and vote in order to decide where the WCA World Championship 2019 will take place. If any Director will be involved in a team that sends in an application, he will be replaced in the selection process by another person (for example a Senior Delegate or a Committee/Team Leader).\r\n\r\nWe are looking for a competition that can reinforce our concept of large WCA competitions, boost the professionalization of our organization, and is able to give the competitors the best possible experience and the world the best possible show.','2018-05-08 03:36:13',1,'applications-for-world-championship-2019',0,'Applications for World Championship 2019',NULL,'2018-07-17 11:18:00'),
(9441,1273,'The [WCA South American Championship 2018](https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/competitions/SouthAmericanChampionship2018) will take place on December 15 - 16, 2018 in Po, SP, Brazil. Check out the [WCA South American Championship 2018 website](https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/competitions/SouthAmericanChampionship2018) for more information and registration.','2018-05-08 16:53:00',1,'wca-south-american-championship-2018-on-december-15-16-2018-in-poa-sp-brazil',0,'WCA South American Championship 2018 on December 15 - 16, 2018 in Po, SP, Brazil',NULL,'2018-12-17 17:20:22'),
(9524,1338,'The WCT is seeking a new member to help with graphics design for social media posts and other projects!\r\n\r\nThe application is open to all WCA members. You do not have to hold a current position to be considered. This position is directed to those with graphic design experience and duties once on the team will mainly focus on that type of work.\r\n\r\n**What does the WCT do?**\r\n- Answers daily inquires to the WCA through emails and the contact page on the WCA website.\r\n- Manages official WCA social media platforms through frequent & engaging posts\r\n- Works with other WCA leaders to improve the WCA website and communications to the community\r\n- The rights and duties of WCT from our By-laws can be found [here](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1WoMypP_o06DXhJ8jvZ2pcsWgN_bG0zyjSnsBlyY8ls8/edit?usp=sharing).\r\n\r\n**Workflow Outline**\r\n- Social media posts are planned at least 1 week in advance and are posted when members are available. \r\n- Internal emails regarding other WCT projects are answered within 48 hours and other work may come from those projects that take various amounts of time.\r\n- Time commitment per week is between 4-10 hours.\r\n- Must be familiar with Adobe Illustrator, GIMP, or equivalent programs\r\n\r\n**Characteristics we are looking for**\r\n- Creativity: *We always need ideas of new social media series or unique ways to expand to other platforms. You will be required to think about this and suggest ideas when you can. With your graphic design experience, you will help us with designing visually compelling posts.*\r\n- Social media knowledge: *You should be familiar with many social media platforms and their basic functions. While you may not have used them personally, you will have to post to them as the WCA and should know what type of content goes on each.*\r\n- Fluent English: *Our posts on most social media platforms are in English and we answer most emails in English. We do welcome those that are fluent in other languages alongside English.*\r\n- Communication skills: *You will be responsible for designing social media posts that are appropriate and convey the mission of the WCA.*\r\n- Patience: *You should keep friendly communications within our email and social media interactions.*\r\n\r\n**To apply, please include:**\r\n- A brief personal introduction\r\n- Your involvement with the WCA\r\n- Your motivation for applying to the WCT\r\n- 2-3 designs that you have created to highlight your design style\r\n- An example design for a WCA posting about the first competition in a new country\r\n\r\n**Please send the application in PDF format to [lmclement55@gmail.com](mailto:lmclement55@gmail.com) from now until June 3, 2018, 23:59 UTC to be considered.**\r\n\r\nThere may be an additional interview requested of candidates with the leader following application submission. The week after the application period, the team will make a selection and the new member(s) will be announced once candidates have accepted the positions.\r\n\r\nThank you for your candidacies and support!','2018-05-21 04:31:20',1,'call-for-applicants-wct-graphic-designer-may-2018',0,'Call for Applicants - WCT Graphic Designer (May 2018)',NULL,'2019-07-02 12:06:24'),
(9531,1338,'We are happy to announce that we have a new Committee Leader. Chris Wright will replace Chris Hardwick as the Leader of the WCA Financial Committee (WFC), and thus as the WCA Treasurer. Chris Wright was already working as a member of the WFC, and will step down as a member of the WCA Ethics Committee.\r\n\r\nChris Wright was selected by the WCA Board and approved in a voting among the current Committee/Team Leaders and Senior Delegates, following Section 4 of our [Motion 10.2017.0 ](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1NDLzup8rbfw8En0S6vtChNti9IKopDBq/edit)about WCA Committees and Teams.\r\n\r\nWe thank Chris Hardwick for the great work he has done for the WCA, and wish Chris Wright the best of luck in fulfilling his new duties.\r\n\r\nThe new Leader will be promoted immediately. Chris Wright was the only applicant, and his candidacy document can be found [here](https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/13LrXkIzm0IWT-3lfW3twNj_VUT4dIQHr?usp=sharing) if you are interested in viewing it. ','2018-05-22 00:31:45',1,'new-wfc-leader',0,'New WFC Leader',NULL,'2018-06-09 17:11:48'),
(9793,1338,'We hereby announce that as of June 30, 2018, the WCA Board of Directors is reduced to three members. Luis J. Iezs term has officially ended, and Pedro Santos Guimares and Ron van Bruchem stepped down from their positions as Board members.\r\n<!-- break -->\r\nWe deeply thank Luis, Pedro, and Ron for their efforts and for the great work they have done for the WCA to convert it to what it is now. A special mention goes to Ron, who co-founded the World Cube Association, and has dedicated almost 15 years of his life to spread the WCA Mission and Spirit around the world. We wish the three of them the best of luck on all of their future projects!\r\n','2018-07-01 18:53:18',1,'changes-in-the-wca-board',0,'Changes in the WCA Board',NULL,'2018-07-09 06:36:03'),
(9794,1338,'There will be an appointment of a new WCA Ethics Committee Leader, as Hippolyte Moreau recently stepped down as the Leader of the WCA Ethics Committee. We thank Hippolyte for his work getting the WEC established in the past months. \r\n<!-- break -->\r\nCandidates are expected to fulfill their terms (24 months) and to spend at least 6 hours per week on average to work for the Committee. The qualities expected of candidates are:\r\n          1. Clear background\r\n          2. Trustworthiness\r\n          3. Independence\r\n          4. Accountability\r\n\r\nThe application period is opened for candidates to submit their candidacy documents until **July 16th, 2018, 23:59 UTC** privately to the WCA Board ([board@worldcubeassociation.org](mailto:board@worldcubeassociation.org)).\r\n\r\nThe candidacy documents must be in PDF format, and must include:\r\n          - Brief personal introduction.\r\n          - Summary of activities done for the WCA.\r\n          - Ambitions as the WEC Leader of the WCA.\r\n\r\nCandidates are additionally asked to send a copy of their applications which can be made public at the end of the application period.\r\n\r\nThe rights and duties of the WEC can be found in [WCA Motion 10.2017.8](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1nYX6qrEB8vDCd2xX8s0xdMCyVFPOCadw/edit). \r\n\r\nThe week after the application period, the WCA Board will make a selection by voting and will announce the new Leader, after confirmation among Senior Delegates and sitting Committee/Team Leaders by voting, as described in [Section 4 of WCA Motion 10.2017.0](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1NDLzup8rbfw8En0S6vtChNti9IKopDBq/edit).\r\n\r\nThank you in advance for your candidacies and support!','2018-07-01 19:00:26',1,'appointment-of-new-wec-leader-july-2018',0,'Appointment of New WEC Leader (July 2018)',NULL,'2019-07-02 12:09:50'),
(9803,10,'`TNoodle-WCA-0.13.4` is now available from https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/regulations/scrambles/\r\nThe following changes have been made since `TNoodle-WCA-0.13.3`:\r\n\r\n- Multiple Blindfolded rounds are no longer generated with a default number of puzzles. The person generating scrambles for a competition will have to pick a sufficiently high number based on expected competitors.\r\n- TNoodle no longer generates extra scrambles for Fewest Moves in the JSON data for the scrambles.\r\n- The Fewest Moves sheet translation for Korean has been updated.\r\n- Event names on the legacy scramble UI now match the Regulations.\r\n- A \"scramble group\" is now called a \"scramble set\", to avoid confusion with competitor groups.\r\n- A broken favicon link in the new UI has been fixed.\r\n\r\nUpcoming competitions should use `TNoodle-WCA-0.13.4` to generate new scrambles, when possible.\r\nHowever, since there are no changes that directly affect competitors since the previous version, `TNoodle-WCA-0.13.3` will briefly remain an officially permitted version. (Competition scrambles for the coming week that have already been generated using `TNoodle-WCA-0.13.3` can still be used.)\r\n\r\nPlease remember that official competitions must use a current version of the official scramble program. This is always available from:\r\nhttps://www.worldcubeassociation.org/regulations/scrambles/','2018-07-02 23:45:06',1,'tnoodle-0-13-4',0,'TNoodle 0.13.4',NULL,'2018-07-10 01:22:40'),
(9851,10,'When `TNoodle-WCA-0.13.4` was released last week, we announced that `TNoodle-WCA-0.13.3` would briefly remain an officially permitted version. Since a week has passed, `TNoodle-WCA-0.13.3` is now officially retired, leaving `TNoodle-WCA-0.13.4` as the only official scramble program.\r\n\r\nPlease see [last week\'s `TNoodle-WCA-0.13.4`  announcement](https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/posts/tnoodle-0-13-4) for details.\r\n\r\nPlease remember that official competitions must use a current version of the official scramble program. This is always available from:\r\nhttps://www.worldcubeassociation.org/regulations/scrambles/','2018-07-10 01:20:24',1,'retiring-tnoodle-0-13-3',0,'Retiring TNoodle 0.13.3',NULL,'2018-07-10 01:22:18'),
(9868,1338,'The successful passing of the recent amendments to the Motions has established the WCA Marketing Team that is in need of a leader. **The WCA Marketing Team (WMT)** is an Advisory Committee of the WCA which is responsible for developing and managing the WCA Brand, seeking sponsorships, supporting the distribution of WCA Competition Gear, and marketing WCA Merchandise.\r\n<!--break-->\r\nCandidates are expected to fulfill their terms (24 months) and to spend at least 6 hours per week on average to work for the Team. The qualities expected of candidates are:\r\n      1. Marketing background\r\n      2. Social media knowledge\r\n      3. Fluent English\r\n      4. Communication skills\r\n\r\nThe application period is open for candidates to submit their candidacy documents until **July 31st, 2018, 23:59 UTC** privately to the WCA Board ([board@worldcubeassociation.org](mailto:board@worldcubeassociation.org)).\r\n\r\nThe candidacy documents must be in PDF format, and must include:\r\n      - Brief personal introduction.\r\n      - Summary of activities done for the WCA.\r\n      - Ambitions as the WMT Leader.\r\n\r\nCandidates are additionally asked to send a copy of their applications which can be made public at the end of the application period.\r\n\r\nThe rights and duties of the WMT are copied from [WCA Motion 10.2018.1](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1_Cnyl6b248_qgFDPtklWCPpxDjfmCMQ7/view).\r\n\r\nThe week after the application period, the WCA Board will make a selection by voting and will announce the new Leader, after confirmation among Senior Delegates and sitting Committee/Team Leaders by voting, as described in Section 4 of [WCA Motion 10.2017.0](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1NDLzup8rbfw8En0S6vtChNti9IKopDBq/edit).\r\n\r\nThank you in advance for your candidacies and support!\r\n','2018-07-14 19:29:44',1,'appointment-of-new-wmt-leader-july-2018',0,'Appointment of New WMT Leader (July 2018)',NULL,'2019-07-02 12:09:37'),
(9894,8698,'The application period for WCA World Championship 2019 has ended. Thank you to everyone who submitted their application documents! Here are the list of the cities that applied:\r\n\r\nBeijing or Guangzhou, China\r\nBrest, Belarus\r\nMelbourne, Australia\r\n\r\nThe selection team will be the Board members: Olivr Perge (process leader), Alberto Prez de Rada Fiol, and Bob Burton. \r\n\r\nThe selection process will consist of individual evaluations of the applications, interviews with the applicants, and finally a vote by the selection team. The goal is to come to an agreement about the winning applicant, so that we can proceed with confidence that the competition will be successful and a positive experience for all who attend.\r\n\r\nOnce the selection is finalized, another announcement will be made before the end of August.','2018-07-17 17:50:26',1,'candidates-for-wca-world-championship-2019',0,'Candidates for WCA World Championship 2019',NULL,'2018-08-31 04:00:03'),
(9943,2,'[Mats Valk](https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/persons/2007VALK01) won the [WCA European Championship 2018](https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/competitions/Euro2018) with an average of 7.24 seconds. [Sebastian Weyer](https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/persons/2010WEYE02) finished second (7.36) and [Philipp Weyer](https://www.worldcubeassociation.org/persons/2010WEYE01) finished third (7.37).\r\n\r\nWorld records: Daniel Rose-Levine&lrm; 3x3x3 With Feet 22.22 (average), Juan Pablo Huanqui&lrm; Megaminx 29.49 (single).  \r\nEuropean records: Amos Nordman&lrm; Megaminx 36.09 (average), Ciarn Beahan&lrm; 6x6x6 Cube 1:32.71 (average), dm Barta&lrm; 3x3x3 Blindfolded 24.06 (average).  \r\nSouth American records: Juan Pablo Huanqui&lrm; Megaminx 34.25 (average), Megaminx 33.55 (average), Pedro Alejandro Condo Tellez&lrm; 4x4x4 Cube 28.81 (average), 4x4x4 Cube 28.69 (average), 5x5x5 Cube 44.81 (single), 5x5x5 Cube 42.40 (single), 6x6x6 Cube 1:32.36 (single), 6x6x6 Cube 1:40.81 (average).  \r\n','2018-07-23 19:12:48',1,'mats-valk-wins-wca-european-championship-2018-in-madrid-spain',0,'Mats Valk wins WCA European Championship 2018, in Madrid, Spain',NULL,'2018-08-10 15:44:57');
